man]] (c.1298-1355), Bishop of Norwich and founder of Trinity Hall, Cambridge\n\n==Fictional characters==\n*Danny Bateman, a character in the football film [[The Replacements (film)|''The Replacements'']]\n*[[Patrick Bateman]], a recurring character in the works of Bret Easton Ellis and protagonist of the book ''American Psycho''\n*[[Sean Bateman]], brother of Patrick Bateman and one of the three main characters in ''The Rules of Attraction''\n\n==Other uses==\n*[[Bateman's principle]]\n*[[Batemans Brewery]] (George Bateman and Son, Ltd), Lincolnshire\n\n{{disambiguation|surname|geo}}\n", "name_user": "Graham87", "label": "safe", "comment": "rv same user to last version by DePiep", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bateman"}
{"title_page": "The Fate of the Furious", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 American action film by F. Gary Gray}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Fate of the Furious\n| image          = The Fate of The Furious Theatrical Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[F. Gary Gray]]\n| producer       = {{Plain list |\n* [[Neal H. Moritz]]\n* [[Vin Diesel]]\n* Michael Fottrell\n* [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]]<!--PER CREDITS-->\n}}\n| writer         = Chris Morgan\n| based on       = {{Based on|[[List of The Fast and the Furious characters|Characters]]|[[Gary Scott Thompson]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plain list |\n* Vin Diesel <!-- Do not add link here per MOS:REPEATLINK as Diesel is already linked above. -->\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n* [[Jason Statham]]\n* [[Michelle Rodriguez]]\n* [[Tyrese Gibson]]\n* [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]]\n* [[Scott Eastwood]]\n* [[Nathalie Emmanuel]]\n* [[Elsa Pataky]]\n* [[Kurt Russell]]\n* [[Charlize Theron]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Brian Tyler]]\n| cinematography = [[Stephen F. Windon]]\n| editing        = {{Unbulleted list|[[Christian Wagner]]|[[Paul Rubell]]}}\n| studio         = {{Unbulleted list|[[Original Film]]|[[One Race Films]] |[[China Film Group Corporation|China Film]]}}\n| distributor    = [[Universal Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2017|4|4|[[Berlin]]|2017|4|14|United States}}\n| runtime        = {{Plain list |\n* 136 minutes (theatrical release)\n* 148 minutes (director's cut)\n}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $250 million<ref name=\"2017FFS\">{{Cite journal |date= August 2018 |title= 2017 Feature Film Study |url= https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/2017_film_study_v3-WEB.pdf |journal= FilmL.A. Feature Film Study |page= 25 |accessdate= August 9, 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"DEADopen\" />\n| gross          = $1.236&nbsp;billion<ref>{{cite web |title= The Fate of the Furious (14 April 2017) |work= [[Boxoffice (magazine)|Boxoffice]] |url= http://pro.boxoffice.com/movie/29210/the-fate-of-the-furious |accessdate= May 7, 2018 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Fate of the Furious''''' (alternatively known as '''''F8''''' and '''''Fast & Furious 8''''') is a 2017 American [[action film]] directed by [[F. Gary Gray]] and written by [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]]. A sequel to 2015's ''[[Furious 7]]'', it is the eighth installment in the ''[[Fast & Furious]]'' franchise and stars [[Vin Diesel]], [[Dwayne Johnson]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Michelle Rodriguez]], [[Tyrese Gibson]], [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]], [[Scott Eastwood]], [[Nathalie Emmanuel]], [[Elsa Pataky]], [[Kurt Russell]] and [[Charlize Theron]]. ''The Fate of the Furious'' follows [[Dominic Toretto]] (Diesel), who has settled down with his wife [[Letty Ortiz]] (Rodriguez), until [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] Cipher (Theron) coerces him into working for her and turns him against his team, forcing them to find Dom and take down Cipher.\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' marks the first installment in the franchise since ''[[The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift]]'' (2006) not to feature [[Paul Walker]], who died on November 30, 2013 in a [[single-vehicle crash]] while the filming of ''Furious 7'' was still in progress<ref>{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Hazel|title=Paul Walker died due to road accident|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3020710/Death-Fast-Furious-star-Paul-Walker-solely-actions-driver-friend-Porsche-claims-lawsuit.html|work=[[Daily Mail]]|date=April 1, 2015|accessdate=May 25, 2015}}</ref> Script rewrites to the seventh installment after Walker's death were intended to complete the story arc for his character, [[Brian O'Conner]].\n\nPlans for an eighth installment were first announced in March 2015 when Diesel appeared on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'' and announced that the film would be set in New York City. Preparations for the film began immediately after the release of ''Furious 7'', with Diesel, Morgan, and producer [[Neal H. Moritz]] re-signing. After setting an initial release date in the same month, casting took place between April and June 2015. In October 2015, Gray was announced to direct the film in the place of [[James Wan]], who had directed the previous installment. [[Principal photography]] began in March 2016 in locations such as [[M\u00fdvatn]], [[Havana]], [[Atlanta]], [[Cleveland]], and New York City, continuing the franchise's tradition of filming in exotic locations around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Where was The Fate of the Furious filmed?|url=http://www.atlasofwonders.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-furious-filming-locations.html|work=Atlas of Wonders|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' premiered in [[Berlin]] on April 4, 2017 and was theatrically released in conventional and [[IMAX]] theaters in the United States on April 14, 2017 while also playing in [[3D film|3D]], [[IMAX 3D]], and [[4DX]] internationally. The film received mixed reviews from critics, many of whom praised the performances and action sequences, but criticized the storyline. The film grossed over $1.2&nbsp;billion worldwide, making it the thirtieth film (and the second in the franchise, after ''Furious 7'') to gross over $1&nbsp;billion, the [[2017 in film#Highest grossing films|third-highest-grossing film of 2017]] and the [[List of highest-grossing films|nineteenth highest-grossing film of all time]]. It also grossed $541.9&nbsp;million worldwide during its opening weekend, which made it the [[list of highest-grossing openings for films|highest-grossing worldwide opening of all time]] until the release of ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' the following year. \n\nA sequel, ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]'', is scheduled to be released on April 2, 2021.\n\n== Plot ==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for feature-length films should be between 400 and 700 words. -->\nFollowing the defeat of [[Deckard Shaw]] and Mose Jakande,{{refn|group=N|As depicted in the 2015 film ''[[Furious 7]]''.}} [[Dominic Toretto|Dominic \"Dom\" Toretto]] and Letty Ortiz are on their honeymoon in [[Havana]] when Dom's cousin Fernando gets in trouble owing money to local racer Raldo. Sensing Raldo is a [[loan shark]], Dom challenges Raldo to a race, pitting Fernando's reworked car against Raldo's, and wagering his own Third Generation [[Chevrolet Impala]]. After narrowly winning the race, Dom allows Raldo to keep his car, earning his respect, and instead leaves his cousin with his car.\n\nThe next day, Dom is approached by the elusive [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] Cipher who coerces him into working for her by showing him an unseen photo. Shortly afterwards, Dom and his team, comprising Letty, Roman Pearce, Tej Parker, and Ramsey, are recruited by [[Diplomatic Security Service]] (DSS) agent Luke Hobbs to help him retrieve an [[Electromagnetic pulse|EMP device]] from a military outpost in [[Berlin]]. During the getaway, Dom goes rogue, forcing Hobbs off the road and stealing the device for Cipher. Hobbs is arrested and locked up in the same high-security prison in which he helped imprison Shaw. After Shaw and Hobbs both escape the prison, they are recruited by intelligence operative [[List of The Fast and the Furious characters#Mr. Nobody|Mr. Nobody]] and his prot\u00e9g\u00e9 to help the team find Dom and capture Cipher. Shaw reveals that Cipher had hired his brother Owen to steal the Nightshade device and Mose Jakande to steal God's Eye, Ramsey's software program. The team tracks Dom and Cipher to their very location just as the latter two attack the base, causing injuries to the team, and stealing God's Eye. Roman suggests bringing [[Brian O'Conner|Brian]] in to help them, but Letty rejects the idea as they agreed not to bring him and Mia into any more missions for the sake of their children.\n\nWhen Dom questions Cipher's motives, she reveals that she has been holding hostage Dom's ex-lover and DSS agent Elena Neves\u2014as well as their son, of whose existence Dom was previously unaware. Elena tells Dom that she wanted him to decide the child's first name, having already given him the middle name Marcos.\n\nIn New York City, Cipher sends Dom to retrieve a [[nuclear football]] held by the [[Ministry of Defense (Russia)|Russian Minister of Defense]]. Prior to the theft, Dom briefly evades Cipher\u2014with the help of Raldo\u2014and persuades Shaw's mother, Magdalene Shaw, to help him. Cipher hacks into the electronics systems of a large number of cars, causing them to disable the convoy so that Dom can take the football. The team intercepts Dom, but Dom escapes, shooting and apparently killing Shaw in the process. Letty catches up to Dom, but is ambushed and nearly killed by Cipher's enforcer, Connor Rhodes, before Dom rescues her. In retaliation, Cipher has Rhodes execute Elena in front of a helpless Dom.\n\nDom infiltrates a base in Russia to use the EMP device to disable their security and then to disable a [[nuclear submarine]], enabling Cipher to hijack it and attempt to use its arsenal to trigger a nuclear war. They are once again intercepted by the team, who attempt to shut down the sub, and then drive out toward the gates that would prevent the sub from leaving into open waters. Meanwhile, Shaw, whose death was faked, teams up with Owen, and at Magdalene's behest, infiltrates Cipher's plane to rescue Dom's son. Once Shaw reports that the child is safe, Dom turns on Cipher and kills Rhodes, before rejoining his team. Infuriated, Cipher fires an [[infrared homing]] missile at Dom, but he breaks away from his team and maneuvers around it, causing the missile to hit the submarine instead. The team quickly forms a vehicular blockade around Dom, shielding him from the ensuing explosion. Shaw reaches the front of the plane and confronts Cipher, who jumps from the plane with a parachute.\n\nMr. Nobody and his prot\u00e9g\u00e9 visit Dom and his team in New York City to report that Cipher is still at large in [[Athens]]. Hobbs is offered his DSS job back, but he declines in order to spend more time with his daughter. Shaw delivers Dom his son, putting his differences aside with Dom and Hobbs. \n\nDom names his son Brian, after his friend and brother-in-law [[Brian O'Conner]], and celebrates with his friends.\n\n==Cast==\n{{details|topic=the characters|List of Fast & Furious characters}}\n* [[Vin Diesel]] as [[Dominic Toretto]], a former criminal and professional street racer who has retired and settled down with his wife, Letty. He is [[coerced]] by Cipher to work against his team.\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]] as [[Luke Hobbs]], a [[Diplomatic Security Service]] (DSS) agent who allied with Dom and his team following their outings in [[Rio de Janeiro]] and Europe.\n* [[Jason Statham]] as [[Deckard Shaw]], a rogue British Special Forces assassin who was imprisoned by Hobbs and the DSS after his defeat in Los Angeles, who serves as an ally to help Dom's team take down Cipher.\n* [[Michelle Rodriguez]] as [[Letty Ortiz]], Dom's wife and a former professional street racer.\n* [[Tyrese Gibson]] as [[Roman Pearce]], a former criminal from [[Barstow, California|Barstow]] and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]] as [[Tej Parker]], a mechanic from Miami and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Scott Eastwood]] as Eric Reisner / Little Nobody,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/2017/4/9/15218064/fast-and-furious-8-fate-of-the-furious-review|title=Fast and Furious 8: 5 things to know about The Fate of the Furious|last=Abad-Santos |first=Alex|date=April 11, 2017|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/fate-of-the-furious-ending-post-credit-scene|title=What the Ending of 'The Fate of the Furious' Could Mean for the 'Fast' Franchise|first=Dan|last=Jackson|date=April 18, 2017|website=[[Thrillist]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> a law enforcement agent working under Mr. Nobody.\n* [[Nathalie Emmanuel]] as Ramsey, a computer [[Hacktivism|hacktivist]] and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Elsa Pataky]] as Elena Neves, the mother of Dom's child and a former Rio de Janeiro police officer who moved to the United States to become Hobbs' new partner at the DSS.\n* [[Kurt Russell]] as Mr. Nobody,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagonow.com/seven-gunn-says/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-ff8/|title=The Fate of the Furious Review: FF8|author=Seven Gunn Says|date=April 14, 2017|website=[[ChicagoNow]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> an intelligence operative and the leader of a covert ops team which previously aided Dom and his team in taking down Deckard in [[Abu Dhabi]].\n* [[Charlize Theron]] as Cipher, a criminal mastermind and [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] who coerces Dom into working against his team by holding Elena and their son hostage.\n\n[[Tego Calder\u00f3n]] and [[Don Omar]] reprise their respective roles as Tego Leo and Rico Santos, former members of Dom's team, from previous films. [[Kristofer Hivju]] portrays Connor Rhodes, Cipher's enforcer and right-hand man, and [[Patrick St. Esprit]] appears as DS Allen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.militarypress.com/the-fate-of-the-furious-revs-up-the-engines-again/|title='The Fate of the Furious' revs up the engines again|last=Jacquin|first=Jeri|date=April 14, 2017|website=MilitaryPress|accessdate=November 7, 2017}}</ref> [[Luke Evans (actor)|Luke Evans]] reprises his role from ''[[Fast & Furious 6]]'' (2013) and ''[[Furious 7]]'' (2015) as Owen Shaw, Deckard's younger brother and a former [[Special Air Service]] (SAS) soldier who formerly opposed Dom's team in Europe, and who helps his brother in rescuing Dom's son. [[Helen Mirren]] makes an uncredited [[cameo appearance]] as Magdalene Shaw, the mother of Deckard and Owen Shaw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1635570/how-helen-mirren-ended-up-in-the-fate-of-the-furious-according-to-vin-diesel|title=How Helen Mirren Ended Up in the Fate of the Furious, According To Vin Diesel|last=Wakeman|first=Gregory|date=March 14, 2017|website=CinemaBlend|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> Celestino Cornielle portrays Raldo, a street racer whose respect Dom earns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiddenremote.com/2017/04/30/celestino-cornielle-road-fate-furious/|title=Celestino Cornielle On His Road To \u2018The Fate Of The Furious\u2019|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nFollowing the release of ''[[Furious 7]]'' (2015), [[Vin Diesel]] said regarding a possible sequel:\n\n{{quote|text=I was trying to keep it close to the vest throughout the release. [[Paul Walker]] used to say that [an eighth film] was guaranteed. And in some ways, when your brother guarantees something, you sometimes feel like you have to make sure it comes to pass ... so if fate has it, then you'll get this when you hear about it. [''Furious 7''] was for Paul, [the eighth film] is from Paul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/2015/04/13/vin-diesel-says-furious-7-was-for-paul-and-8-will-be-from-paul/|title=Vin Diesel Says Furious 7 Was For Paul And 8 Will Be From Paul|author=Joe Comicbook|work=Comicbook.com}}</ref>|sign=|source=}}\n\n{{quote box|width=27%|align=right|quote=We're trying to do what we always do, which is try to come at it from a character point of view and figure out where the characters would go from here. I think the thing that's made ''[[The Fast and the Furious]]'' special is obviously we have incredible action and so on. But the thing that people really relate to the most is the characters. We're lucky that we have a lot of great characters. Unfortunately, we don't have Paul [Walker] anymore. His character... has moved on. But we feel like there's a lot still to be mined. That's where we're starting. We're really talking about the characters, where they all sit right now. It's a huge challenge.|source=\u2014[[Neal H. Moritz]], ''The Fast and the Furious'' franchise producer<ref name=\"Characters\">{{cite web|last=Yaniz|first=Robert, Jr.|title='Furious 8' Producer Discusses Continuing Without Paul Walker|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-furious-8-paul-walker/|work=Screen Rant|date=July 22, 2015|accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref>}}\n\nDiesel further hinted at an eighth film on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'' when he stated that [[Kurt Russell]]'s character would span multiple films. He also stated that the next film would take place in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/fast-and-furious-8-setting-kurt-russell/|title=Vin Diesel Teases Fast and Furious 8 Setting in New York|work=Slashfilm|date=March 31, 2015|accessdate=March 31, 2015}}</ref> [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]] returned to write his sixth script in the franchise, while [[Neal H. Moritz]] returned to produce. Moritz later stated, \"[The story] is going to have to be something enticing for all of us. It has to be as good as or better [than ''Furious 7'']\".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-8-nowhere-starting-line-787045 | title='Fast 8' Nowhere Near Starting Line | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=April 8, 2015 | accessdate=April 21, 2015 | first1=Rebecca |last1=Ford |first2=Borys |last2=Kit}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2015 [[CinemaCon]] in [[Las Vegas]], Diesel announced the film for an April 14, 2017 release date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/furious-8-gets-2017-release-791103|title='Furious 8' Gets 2017 Release Date|first=Rebecca |last=Ford|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=April 24, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/furious-8-to-debut-april-14-2017-1201478792/|title='Furious 8' to Debut April 14, 2017|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=April 24, 2015}}</ref> On August 16, 2015, at the [[2015 Teen Choice Awards]] (where ''Furious 7'' received the award for [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie - Action|Choice Movie \u2013 Action]] and Walker received the award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Action), Diesel gave the film the initial title ''Fast 8''.<ref>{{cite web|last=O'Connell|first=Sean|title=Vin Diesel Just Dropped The Name of the Next Fast & Furious Movie|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Vin-Diesel-Just-Dropped-Name-Next-Fast-Furious-Movie-77617.html|work=Cinema Blend|date=August 17, 2015|accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref> In September 2015, Diesel stated that the script had almost been completed,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Busch|first1=Anita|title=Will Vin Diesel Direct 'Furious 8'?|url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/vin-diesel-furious-8-director-universal-1201558992/|accessdate=October 7, 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=October 1, 2015}}</ref> and expressed interest in [[Rob Cohen]], who directed the [[The Fast and the Furious (2001 film)|first film]], to direct the eighth installment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vin Diesel Wants Rob Cohen to Direct Furious 8|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/618557-vin-diesel-wants-rob-cohen-to-direct-furious-8|accessdate=October 4, 2015|work=comingsoon.net|date=October 1, 2015}}</ref> On October 14, 2015, Diesel announced on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' that ''[[Straight Outta Compton (film)|Straight Outta Compton]]'' director [[F. Gary Gray]] would direct the film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Silver|first=Stephen|title=Fast and Furious 8: Vin Diesel Re-Confirms New York Setting|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-and-furious-8-new-york-setting-vin-diesel/|work=Screen Rant|date=October 16, 2015|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=VIDEO: Vin Diesel Reveals Setting & Director for 'FAST 8' on Tonight Show|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/VIDEO-Vin-Diesel-Reveals-Setting-Director-for-FAST-8-on-Tonight-Show-20151015|work=BWW TV World|date=October 15, 2015|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, Moritz said that Walker's character, Brian O'Conner, would not appear in the film, following the use of [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] in the previous film after Walker died in a [[single-vehicle accident]] on November 30, 2013, with Moritz stating that his character had \"moved on\".<ref name=\"Characters\"/> It had previously been reported that Paul's younger brother, [[Cody Walker (actor)|Cody Walker]], would either join the cast in a new role,<ref>{{cite web|last=Jordan|first=Shane|title='Fast and Furious 8' Paul Walker Brother Cody Cast in New Role?|url=http://www.classicalite.com/articles/23888/20150613/fast-furious-8-paul-walker-brother-cody-cast-new-role.htm|work=Classicalite|date=June 13, 2015|accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref> or replace his older brother in the role of O'Conner;<ref>{{cite web|last=Monalo|first=Komfie|title=Fast and Furious 8 Release Date, Cast: Will Cody Walker Replace Paul Walker (Brian O'Conner)?|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/56362/20150702/fast-furious-8-release-date-cast-will-cody-walker-replace-paul-brian-oconnor.htm|work=Gospel Herald|date=July 2, 2013|accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref> however, it was later announced that the character will not return to the franchise.<ref>{{cite web|last=Agpalo|first=Jaja|title='Fast and Furious 8' Release Date & Cast: Cody Walker Not Returning; Will The Plot Still Include Paul Walker? Plus, Other Details We Know [VIDEO]|url=http://www.foodworldnews.com/articles/52975/20151112/fast-furious-8-release-date-cast-cody-walker-returning-will.htm|work=Food World News|date=November 12, 2015|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref> Moritz also said that the film would shift the focus of the franchise from a series of [[heist film]]s to a [[Spy film|spy caper]], following a similar change in focus from [[street racing]] in ''[[Fast Five]]'' (2011).<ref>{{cite web|last=Sokol|first=Tony|title=Fast & Furious 8 Movie Casting News: 'Fast and Furious 8' Will Begin New Trilogy As Soon As They Find A Director, Which Hinges On Finding Screenplay|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/226898/20150803/fast-furious-8-movie-casting-news-will-begin-new-trilogy.htm|work=KpopStarz|date=August 3, 2015|accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref> In December 2016, the film was retitled ''The Fate of the Furious''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-8-retitled-fate-of-the-furious-trailer-teaser-arrives/|title=Fast 8 Retitled Fate of the Furious; Trailer Teaser Arrives|work=Screen Rant|date=December 9, 2016|accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nDiesel, Russell and [[Michelle Rodriguez]] were the first to confirm their involvement in the film, and [[Tyrese Gibson]] and [[Ludacris|Chris Bridges]] both confirmed their return soon after.<ref>{{cite web|last=Das|first=Chandan|title='Fast & Furious 8' Cast News, Release Date: Eva Mendes As Undercover Agent Monica Fuentes|url=http://www.breathecast.com/articles/fast-furious-8-cast-news-and-release-date-eva-mendes-to-return-as-undercover-agent-monica-29152/|work=BreatheCast|date=June 29, 2015|accessdate=July 2, 2015}}</ref> [[Lucas Black]] had signed on to reprise his role from ''[[The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift]]'' as Sean Boswell for ''Furious 7'', and two more instalments in September 2013, though he did not appear in ''Fate''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Eisenberg|first=Eric|title=Lucas Black Signs On For Fast & Furious 7, 8 And 9|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Lucas-Black-Signs-Fast-Furious-7-8-9-39448.html|work=Cinema Blend|date=September 16, 2013|accessdate=July 2, 2015}}</ref> In May 2015, [[Dwayne Johnson]] confirmed his involvement in the film, additionally hinting at a possible spin-off film involving his character, Luke Hobbs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast & Furious 8: Dwayne Johnson confirms his return|url=http://www.msn.com/en-gb/entertainment/story/fast-and-furious-8-dwayne-johnson-confirms-his-return/ar-BBjWpJw?ocid=MSNCOEO|publisher=[[MSN]]|date=May 19, 2015|accessdate=June 25, 2015}}</ref> [[Jason Statham]] also confirmed his return.<ref>{{cite web|last=Brew|first=Simon|title=Exclusive: Jason Statham on Crank 3 and Fast & Furious 8|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/jason-statham/35542/exclusive-jason-statham-on-crank-3-and-fast-furious-8|work=[[Den of Geek]]|date=May 28, 2015|accessdate=June 25, 2015}}</ref> In April 2016, [[Charlize Theron]] and [[Kristofer Hivju]] were confirmed as additions to the cast, in villainous roles,<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title=Charlize Theron Joins 'Fast 8'|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/charlize-theron-fast-8-vin-diesel-1201743898/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 7, 2016|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Morrison|first=Sara|title=Kristofer Hivju cast in 'Fast & Furious 8'|url=http://www.hitfix.com/news/kristofer-hivju-cast-in-fast-furious-8|work=Hitfix|date=April 7, 2016|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref> while [[Scott Eastwood]] also joined the film as a law enforcement agent.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/fast-8-new-character-scott-eastwood-starring-1201735483/ | title='Fast 8' Creates New Character; Scott Eastwood To Star | work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]| date=April 11, 2016 | accessdate=April 13, 2016 | author=Mike Fleming Jr}}</ref> On May 17, 2016, Diesel posted a photo on his [[Instagram]] page of himself and [[Elsa Pataky]] on set, indicating that she had also returned for the film,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BFfMtGHmPo2/|title=Instagram photo by Vin Diesel \u2022 May 17, 2016 at 12:00&nbsp;am UTC|work=[[Instagram]]|date=May 17, 2016|accessdate=May 18, 2016}}</ref> and was followed two days later by a video on set with [[Nathalie Emmanuel]], who also starred in the previous film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BFkCMgTmPrA/|title=Instagram video by Vin Diesel \u2022 May 18, 2016 at 9:05&nbsp;pm UTC|work=[[Instagram]]|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 20, 2016}}</ref> In June 2016, [[Helen Mirren]] announced in an interview with ''Elle'' that she would appear in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/movies-tv/news/a37050/helen-mirren-interview/|title=Helen Mirren On Eye in the Sky, and (Exclusive!) the Huge Franchise She'll Star in Next|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=June 15, 2016}}</ref> In July 2016, [[Don Omar]] tweeted that he and [[Tego Calderon]] would return to the franchise for the eighth picture.<ref>{{cite tweet |author= DON OMAR aka KONG  |user= DONOMAR|number= 752522004373307392 |date= July 11, 2016 |title= Is time to work! We are back! @TEGOCALDERON @DONOMAR #LosBandoleros #NewMusicMonday #FF8 |access-date= December 12, 2016}}</ref> During an interview with [[Chris Mannix]] on July 21, 2016, Lucas Black confirmed he would not appear in the eighth instalment, due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://audioboom.com/posts/4846469-the-chris-mannix-show-lucas-black|title=The Chris Mannix Show \u2013 Lucas Black|date=July 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nIn keeping with the franchise's penchant for filming in \"exotic\" locations, such as [[Dubai]] and [[Rio de Janeiro]], in January 2016 it was announced that Universal was seeking approval from the [[Federal government of the United States|United States]] and [[Politics of Cuba|Cuban governments]] to shoot part of the film in [[Cuba]].<ref name=\"Cuba\">{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|last2=Kroll|first2=Justin|title='Fast and Furious 8' Wants to Shoot in Cuba (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/fast-and-furious-8-wants-to-shoot-in-cuba-exclusive-1201672531/|work=Variety|date=January 6, 2016|access-date=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ford|first1=Rebecca|last2=Kit|first2=Borys|title='Fast and Furious 8' to Shoot in Cuba (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-furious-8-shoot-cuba-850559|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=January 6, 2016}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] began on March 14, 2016, in [[M\u00fdvatn]], [[Iceland]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast 8 scenes filmed at M\u00fdvatn|url=http://icelandmonitor.mbl.is/news/culture_and_living/2016/02/22/fast_8_scenes_filmed_at_myvatn/|work=Iceland Monitor|date=February 22, 2016|access-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The car stars of Fast and the Furious 8|url=http://icelandmonitor.mbl.is/news/culture_and_living/2016/03/07/the_car_stars_of_fast_and_the_furious_8/|work=Iceland Monitor|date=March 7, 2016|access-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref> where strong winds sent a plastic iceberg prop flying into a paddock. The prop struck two horses: one was wounded and the other mortally injured; it was later euthanized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/03/14/fast-and-furious-8-horse-iceberg-dead/|title='Fast & Furious 8' Horse Killed By Flying 'Iceberg'|work=[[TMZ.com]]|date=March 14, 2016|access-date=March 16, 2016}}</ref> In late April, filming began in Cuba's capital city, [[Havana]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vin Diesel and Michelle Rodriguez are already in Havana!|url=http://www.cubaheadlines.com/2016-04-20-p13-vin-diesel-and-michelle-rodriguez-are-already-in-havana.html|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=Cuba Headlines|date=April 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fast and Furious Filming in Cuba|url=http://www.havanatimes.org/?p=118318|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=Havana Times.org|date=April 24, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Cruz|first1=Janna Dela|title='Fast and Furious 8' production update: The Rock prepares for return, Michelle Rodriguez, Vin Diesel arrive in Cuba for filming {{!}} Christian News on Christian Today|url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/fast.and.furious.8.production.update.the.rock.prepares.for.return.michelle.rodriguez.vin.diesel.arrive.in.cuba.for.filming/84804.htm|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=christiantoday.com|date=April 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-f-gary-gray-interview-cuba-embargo|title=Is Fate of the Furious's \"Cuban Mile\" Real?|first=Laura|last=Bradley|website=Vanity Fair|access-date=October 25, 2017}}</ref> In May, filming also took place in [[Cleveland]], Ohio.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Morona|first1=Joey|title='Fast & Furious 8' to shoot scenes in Cleveland|url=http://www.cleveland.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2016/03/fast_furious_8_cleveland.html|access-date=April 10, 2016|work=The Plain Dealer|date=March 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Fong|first1=Marvin|title=Filming for 'Fast 8' begins in Cleveland (photos)|url=http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2016/05/filming_for_fast_8_begins_in_c.html|access-date=May 19, 2016|work=The Plain Dealer|date=May 18, 2016}}</ref> Franchise cinematographer [[Stephen F. Windon]] returned for the eighth instalment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stephenwindon.com/home.html|title=Stephen F. Windon ACS ASC \u2013 CINEMATOGRAPHER|website=StephenWindon.com}}</ref> Filming also took place in [[Atlanta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2017/04/13/how-much-did-fast-furious-8-spend-filming-in.html|title=How much did 'Fast & Furious 8' spend filming in Georgia? (SLIDESHOW)|last=Hensley|first=Ellie|date=April 13, 2017|work=Atlanta Business Chronicle|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref> and New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/04/07/fate-furious-exclusive-director-f-gary-gray-new-york-chase/|title='Fate of the Furious' Exclusive: Director F. Gary Gray Previews the Epic New York City Chase|last=Lawrence|first=Derek|date=April 7, 2017|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=October 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\n{{main|The Fate of the Furious (score)|The Fate of the Furious: The Album}}\n[[Brian Tyler]], who scored the third, fourth, fifth, and seventh installments, was tapped to compose the [[film score]] for the eighth picture.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-furious-8-stunts-video-charlize-theron/|title=Fast 8 Stunt Video; Composer Talks Charlize Theron Character|date=June 10, 2016|work=[[Screen Rant]]|accessdate=July 9, 2016}}</ref> A soundtrack album by [[Atlantic Records]] was released on April 14, 2017, coinciding with the film's US theatrical release.<ref>{{cite news|last=Frydenlun|first=Zach|title=Here's ''The Fate of the Furious: The Album'' Soundtrack Tracklist f/ Young Thug, Migos, Travis Scott, and More|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2017/03/fate-of-the-furious-soundtrack-tracklist-exclusive|accessdate=March 10, 2017|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 2, 2017}}</ref> The film's score album was released on April 27, by [[Back Lot Music]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chitwood|first1=Adam|title=Listen to an Exclusive Track from Brian Tyler's ''The Fate of the Furious'' Score|url=http://collider.com/fate-of-the-furious-score-clip-brian-tyler/|accessdate=April 25, 2017|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''The Fate of the Furious'' had its world premiere in [[Berlin]] on April 4, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/hollywood/fate-of-the-furious-to-premiere-at-berlin-on-april-4-fast-and-furious-8-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-4579402/|title=Fate of the Furious to premiere at Berlin on April 4. Vin Diesel shares new poster|work=[[The Indian Express]]|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017}}</ref> The film was theatrically released in the United States on April 14, 2017, playing in [[3D film|3D]], [[IMAX 3D]], and [[4DX]] internationally, and received a day-and-date release across major markets such as Australia, the United Kingdom, China, and [[India]], beginning on April 12, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/universals-fast-8-lands-china-release-date-983382|title=Universal's 'Fast 8' Lands China Release Date (Exclusive)|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 6, 2017|accessdate=March 6, 2017}}</ref> The film was released day-and-date in 1,074 IMAX screens around the world, making it the widest day-and-date opening in IMAX history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4282&p=.htm|title='Boss Baby' Repeats at No. 1 While 'Beauty and the Beast' Closes in on $1 Billion Worldwide|first=Brad |last=Brevet|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' was released on 4K, Blu-ray, DVD, and Digital HD on July 11, 2017, but has yet to be released in 3D Blu-ray.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Fate of the Furious Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/The-Fate-of-the-Furious-Blu-ray/170135/|publisher=[[Blu-ray]]|accessdate=January 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Box office ===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' grossed $226&nbsp;million in the United States and Canada and $1.010&nbsp;billion in other territories for a worldwide total of $1.236&nbsp;billion, against a production budget of $250 million .<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|title=The Fate of the Furious (2017)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=furious8.htm|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=July 14, 2017}}</ref> It is Universal Pictures' most ambitious worldwide distribution release in the studio's history. The film was released day-and-date in 64 territories worldwide, including almost all major markets (minus Japan), starting from April 12, 2017, and was projected to earn anywhere between $375\u2013440&nbsp;million in its five-day opening weekend.<ref name=\"WWW\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-global-opening-box-office-record-furious-7-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202067353/|title='Fate of the Furious' Global Opening Could Leave 'F7's $397M+ Debut in the Dust \u2013 Box Office Preview|first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |first2=Nancy |last2=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"V\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-box-office-opening-1202028227/|title='Fate of the Furious' Races Toward Massive $380 Million-Plus Global Box Office Debut|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> By the end of the weekend, it ended up earning $539.9&nbsp;million from nearly 23,000 screens, way above initial projections, to score [[List of highest-grossing openings for films#Biggest worldwide openings since 2002|the biggest global opening in cinematic history]] until it was surpassed by ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' the following year. It also marked the third time that a film earned over $500&nbsp;million in a single weekend, after ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' ($529&nbsp;million) and ''[[Jurassic World]]'' ($525.5&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"F58\"/> In IMAX, the film made $31.1&nbsp;million from 1,079 screens to record the biggest IMAX April debut and the fourth-biggest overall at the time.<ref name=\"F58\"/>\n\nOn April 30, it crossed the $1&nbsp;billion threshold, becoming the second release of 2017 (following ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]''), the fifth film released by [[Universal Pictures]] (after ''[[Jurassic Park (film)|Jurassic Park]]'', ''[[Furious 7]]'', ''[[Jurassic World]]'', and ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'') and the thirtieth film overall in cinematic history to gross over $1&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"1Billion\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/30/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-joins-furious-7-in-the-1-billion-club/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Joins 'Furious 7' In The $1 Billion Club|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-milestone-fate-furious-crosses-1b-globally-998794|title=Box-Office Milestone: 'Fate of the Furious' Crosses $1B Globally|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> It was the third-highest-grossing film of the year, behind ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]'', and ''Beauty and the Beast'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/19/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-zooms-past-logan-to-be-years-second-biggest-hit/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Zooms Past 'Logan' To Be Year's Second Biggest Hit|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 19, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> the second-biggest action film that is not a fantasy or superhero movie, behind ''Furious 7'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/07/box-office-baahubali-2-drops-68-get-out-tops-200m-fate-of-the-furious-passes-skyfall/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Baahubali 2' Drops 68%, 'Get Out' Tops $200M, 'Fate Of The Furious' Passes 'Skyfall'|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 7, 2017|accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref> and was Universal's highest-grossing live-action release since ''Jurassic World'' back in June 2015.<ref name=\"JJ\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/20/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-nears-700-million-worldwide/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Nears $700 Million Worldwide|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' concluded 2017 as the third highest-grossing film of the year worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/year/2017/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=Domestic Box Office For 2017|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== North America ====\nLike many of its predecessors, ''The Fate of the Furious'' was released in the United States and Canada in the month of April, and like its immediate predecessor, occupied the lucrative [[Easter week]] holiday period slot, where it was expected to open with $100\u2013125&nbsp;million. It received the widest pre-summer release ever, at an estimated 4,304 venues, besting the 4,242 opening theater count of ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'' the previous March.<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-fate-furious-revs-engines-110m-us-debut-993044|title=Box-Office Preview: 'Fate of the Furious' Revs Engines for $110M-Plus U.S. Debut|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-fate-of-the-furious-20170410-htmlstory.html|title='The Fate of the Furious' could reach $400&nbsp;million in global box office this weekend|first=Ryan |last=Faughnde|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/04/12/fate-furious-box-office-predictions/|title=Box office: Fate of the Furious to speed into top spot|first=Joey |last=Nolfi|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> The film made $10.4&nbsp;million from Thursday night previews from 3,310 theaters, the second-highest of the franchise behind ''[[Furious 7]]''{{'}}s $15.8&nbsp;million.<ref name=DEADopen>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|title='Fate of the Furious' To Clock $100M+ Stateside, As Pic Zooms To All-Time $529M+ Global Debut \u2013 Sunday AM Update|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-opening-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202069983/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> On its opening day it grossed $45.6&nbsp;million, with Thursday previews making up 22.8% of the amount, slightly better than the 23% for ''Furious 7''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/15/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-snags-nos-fueled-45-6m-friday-for-likely-100m-weekend/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Snags Boffo $46M Friday For Likely $100M+ Weekend|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Earning a total of $98.8&nbsp;million on its opening weekend, the film scored the second-biggest opening in the franchise (the third-biggest adjusted for inflation) and the third-biggest April debut, behind ''Furious 7'' and ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]''. It posted an almost identical weekend multiplier like its immediate predecessor (2.166\u00d7 vs 2.18\u00d7).<ref name=\"Mul\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/17/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-steals-record-crushing-532m-worldwide-opening/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Steals Record-Crushing $532M Worldwide Opening|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web|url=https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/04/16/movies/fate-of-the-furious-slows-at-home-but-roars-overseas.html?action=click&contentCollection=movies&region=rank&module=package&version=highlights&contentPlacement=2&pgtype=sectionfront&_r=0&referer=https://www.nytimes.com/section/movies|title='Fate of the Furious' Slows at Home but Roars Overseas|first=Brooks |last=Barnes|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref> However, this is not surprising considering how both films opened over Good Friday/Easter Sunday stretch. Scott Mendelson of ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine compared the opening to how ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]'' (2015) opening fell from ''[[Skyfall]]'' (2012). One notable record the film set was the best opening for a film with an African-American director, with Gray besting his own record set with ''[[Straight Outta Compton (film)|Straight Outta Compton]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/16/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-drifts-to-100m-weekend-spark-bombs/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Drifts To $100M Weekend, 'Spark' Bombs|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nSticking to the franchise's famous and lauded habit of including a multi-ethnic cast of characters, the film played to audiences of all ethnicities. Domestically, [[White people|Caucasians]] made up 41 percent of the audience, followed by [[Hispanics]] (26 percent), African-Americans (21 percent), [[Asians]] (11 percent), and Native American/Other (3 percent), according to comScore's exit polling service PostTrack. The pic skewed male at 58 percent, far more than the last film at 51 percent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-fate-furious-nabs-1002m-us-record-5325m-global-start-994377|title=Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Nabs $100.2M in U.S. for Record $532.5M Global Start|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/fate-of-the-furious-box-office-2-1202031577/|title=Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Debuts to Hefty $100.2 Million|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> 2D ticketbuyers represented 57% of the film's opening compared to its predecessor's 71%. This means more die-hard moviegoers came out to watch the eighth instalment rather than people who do not typically go to the movies.<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nWhile ''The Fate of the Furious''{{'}}s debut is 34% less than its predecessor's opening,<ref name=DEADopen/> critics have noted that the debut is still considered a massive success and not a big letdown given it is the eighth installment in an action franchise. [[Universal Pictures]] was well aware that the robust debut of ''Furious 7'' could not be duplicated<ref name=\"NYTimes\"/> due to the wave of good reviews and publicity over the death of star [[Paul Walker]], as well as the notion that the installment was both a farewell to the actor and a kind of coronation for the franchise as a whole. Nevertheless, the film benefited from Easter holiday business with 74% of all K-12 schools off on [[Good Friday]] as well as a third of the nation's colleges.<ref name=DEADopen/> The film comes out in the wake of its parent franchise celebrating 16 years of availability in cinemas. To wit, few film franchises which are close to 20 years old have demonstrated a box office ability to increase their openings with each installment over time or maintain them in close proximity in terms of debut numbers; [[James Bond in film|''James Bond'' film series]], [[Batman in film|''Batman'' film series]], [[Jurassic Park|''Jurassic Park'' franchise]], and [[List of Star Wars films and television series|''Star Wars'' franchise]].<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nIts hefty opening was followed by the second-biggest April Monday gross ever with $8.5&nbsp;million, behind the seventh installment. Its Sunday to Monday drop was 60% compared to its prequel's 57% drop which is far better than the Monday dropped witnessed by other April releases; ''The Jungle Book'' (\u221276%) and ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' (\u221273%), albeit without the advantage of a school holiday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-april-records-global-box-office-1202071688/|title='Fate of the Furious' Posts Second-Best Monday in April Stateside; Drives Past $600M Worldwide|first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/18/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-racing-past-600-million-worldwide/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Racing Past $600 Million Worldwide|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> Despite the entry of four new [[wide release]]s, critics and box office prognosticators kept a close watch on how much the film would drop in its second weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-promise-unforgettable-no-match-furious-8-995693|title=Box-Office Preview: 'The Promise,' 'Unforgettable' No Match for 'Furious 8'|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> The film fell precipitously on its second Friday earning $11.17&nbsp;million for a 76% drop which is the biggest in the franchise's history, besting the 72% drops for both its two immediate predecessors. The steep decline maybe attributed not because of the onslaught of competitions, but rather due to the polarized reception received by the film and due to just 12% K-12 schools beings off compared to 74% on Good Friday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/22/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-plunges-76-on-friday-still-racing-towards-900m/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Plunges 76% On Friday As It Races Towards $900M|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> It kept its hold at No. 1, albeit dropping about 61% in its sophomore frame for an estimated $38.4&nbsp;million. That domestic drop is right in line with the 59\u201363% drops of the six previous installment in the franchise's on their second weekend out.<ref name=\"SW\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-promise-free-fire-born-in-china-unforgettable-phoenix-forgotten-previews-box-office-1202073216/|title='Fate of the Furious' Drives Five Wide Releases Off The Road With $38.6M Second Weekend \u2013 Sunday AM Update|first1=Anita |last1=Busch |first2=Anthony |last2=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> It topped the box office for three straight weekends, witnessing similar weekend-to-weekend percentage drops like its prequel, albeit earning lesser in terms of numbers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-how-to-be-a-latin-lover-1202079002/|title='Latin Lover' Sets $12M Pantelion Record, 'Baahubali 2' Mighty With $10M+, 'Circle' Is A Square As 'F8' Leads Listless Weekend|first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Outside North America ====\nInternationally, ''The Fate of the Furious'' secured a release in 69 countries.<ref name=\"P1\"/> The film was projected to post an opening between $275\u2013330&nbsp;million from over 20,000 screens, with some analysts believing it could go as high as $350\u2013400&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-international-box-office-first-day-1202030112/|title='Fate of the Furious' Races to $19.7 Million on First Day at International Box Office|first=Dave |last=McNarry|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> It opened Wednesday, April 12, 2017, in 8 countries, earning $17.9&nbsp;million (including previews from 12 countries).<ref name=\"P1\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-international-box-office-opening-1202069413/|title=''Fate of the Furious' Gunning Past $430M Overseas; $534M Worldwide For All-Time Opening Records \u2013 International Box Office|first1=Nancy |last1=Tartaglione |first2=Anita |last2=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 15, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> It opened in 33 more countries on Thursday, April 2, for a total of 41 countries, earning $58.4&nbsp;million, marking Universal Pictures overseas' highest-grossing Thursday ever, and for a two-day total of $82.2&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"P1\"/> It added 22 more countries on Friday, April 3, earning $112.1&nbsp;million to score Universal International's highest-grossing Friday of all time, for a three-day total of $194.8&nbsp;million. The robust Friday take helped Universal push past $1&nbsp;billion internationally in 2017 which is the second-quickest ever and the studio's eleventh consecutive year overall the pass the mark. Moreover, on the same day, the franchise crossed the $4&nbsp;billion milestone.<ref name=\"P1\"/> In total, through Sunday, the film registered an opening of $441.1&nbsp;million from 64 markets, setting new records for the biggest April international debut, Universal's biggest, and the biggest of all time overall (ahead of ''[[Jurassic World]]'')\u2014It is the first such film to open past $400&nbsp;million in a single weekend with a bulk of it coming from China. Around $22.6&nbsp;million came from (681) IMAX screens which is Universal's second-biggest behind only ''Jurassic World''.<ref name=\"F58\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-record-opening-weekend-logan-beauty-and-the-beast-international-box-office-1202070697/|title='Fate of the Furious' Smokes Records With $432.3M Overseas Bow; $532.5M Worldwide \u2013 International Box Office|first1=Nancy |last1=Tartaglione |first2=Anita |last2=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> It topped the international charts for a second consecutive term, adding another $158.1&nbsp;million<ref name=\"F908\"/> after which it was surpassed by ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'', another film starring Diesel and Russell, in its third weekend.<ref name=\"GotG\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-2-china-international-box-office-1202079772/|title='Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2' Zooms With $101.2M Bow \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref> In IMAX, the film has grossed north of $58&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"GotG\"/> On May 28, the film officially passed the $1&nbsp;billion threshold to become the second film in the franchise, following ''Furious 7'', and the sixth film to pass the said mark.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/the-fate-of-the-furious-crossing-1-billion-internationally-1202103559/|title='The Fate of the Furious' Expected To Cross $1B Tomorrow at Int'l Box Office|first=Anita |last=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 27, 2017|accessdate=May 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/28/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-races-past-1-billion-overseas/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Races Past $1 Billion Overseas|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 28, 2017|accessdate=May 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIt set the record for the biggest opening day of 2017 in every territory it has been released at, the biggest opening day of all time in 16 markets, Universal's biggest opening day ever in 22 territories and the biggest opening in the franchise in 38 markets. Moreover, it recorded the biggest paid previews of all time in Malaysia, Singapore, Venezuela, and Vietnam.<ref name=\"P1\"/> In terms of opening weekend, the film debuted at No. 1 in all markets where it set the biggest opening weekend of all time in 20 markets; Universal's biggest opening weekend ever in 28 markets; and the biggest opening in the franchise in 40 markets.<ref name=\"F58\"/><ref name=\"F908\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671/|title='Fate of the Furious' Fires Up $745M Offshore, $908M WW; Tops 'Transformers' In China \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-crosses-1-billion-worldwide-box-office-china-record-biggest-grossing-import-1202079768/|title='Fate of the Furious' Drives Past $1B at Worldwide Box Office; Tops 'Furious 7' For New China Record|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> The top openings were recorded in China ($192&nbsp;million),<ref>{{cite news |title=The Fate of the Furious heading for record global opening |url=https://filmindustry.network/fate-furious-heading-record-global-opening/32264 |publisher=Film Industry Network |date=April 16, 2017}}</ref> Mexico ($17.7&nbsp;million), the UK and Ireland ($17.5&nbsp;million), Russia ($14.2&nbsp;million), Germany ($13.6&nbsp;million), Brazil ($12.8&nbsp;million), India ($10.7&nbsp;million), Korea ($10.6&nbsp;million), Middle East combined ($9.9&nbsp;million), Taiwan ($9.3&nbsp;million), France ($9.2&nbsp;million), Australia ($9.5&nbsp;million), Argentina ($9&nbsp;million), Indonesia ($8.5&nbsp;million), Italy ($6.7&nbsp;million), Malaysia ($6.3&nbsp;million), Spain ($6.1&nbsp;million), Colombia ($4.9&nbsp;million), Thailand ($4.9&nbsp;million), Panama ($4.8&nbsp;million),<ref name=\"F58\"/> Pakistan ($2.5&nbsp;million), and Romania ($1.7&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671|title='Fate of the Furious' Fires Up $745M Offshore, $908M WW; Tops 'Transformers' In China \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017}}</ref> Comparing market-to-market performance, ''Furious 7'' had an opening worth $250&nbsp;million without China and Russia while ''The Fate of the Furious'' delivered $228.2&nbsp;million debut, sans the two aforementioned markets.<ref name=\"F58\"/> In Japan, the film debuted with $7.5&nbsp;million. Although that's a new record for the franchise, the film debuted at number three behind Disney's ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' and local film ''[[Detective Conan: Crimson Love Letter]]''\u2014their robust second-weekend earnings blocked the former from taking the top spot, making Japan one of the few markets where the film didn't open at No. 1.<ref name=\"GotG\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/05/03/japan-box-office-blade-of-the-immortal-bombs-detective-conan-keeps-2nd-place|title=Japan Box Office: \"Blade of The Immortal\" Bombs, \"Detective Conan\" Keeps 2nd Place|first=Mikikazu |last=Komatsu|date=May 3, 2017|accessdate=May 4, 2017|work=[[Crunchyroll]]}}</ref>\n\nExpectations were high for the film's performance in China, as its predecessor set notable records and went on to become the biggest film release there (now the biggest Hollywood release). The film was rebranded in Chinese as ''The Fast and the Furious 8'' to make clear its connection to ''Furious 7''. After ticket sales began on April 2, the film pre-sold more than RMB 125 million ($18.1&nbsp;million) worth of tickets before its release, breaking the previous record held by local film ''[[Journey to the West: Conquering the Demons]]'' three months prior. Moreover, it also set a record for the fastest IMAX advance sales, with RMB 16.5&nbsp;million ($2.4&nbsp;million), breaking the previous record held by ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', according to leading local movie site [[Wanda Cinemas|Mtime]].<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fate-furious-sets-chinese-ticket-presales-record-992694|title='The Fate of the Furious' Sets Chinese Ticket Pre-sales Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/can-fate-furious-beat-furious-7-china-box-office-record/|title=Can 'Fate of the Furious' Beat 'Furious 7' China Box Office Record?|first=Matt |last=Pressberg|work=[[The Wrap]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> In total, it pre-sold around $43.5&nbsp;million tickets two hours before previews began, the biggest ever in the country.<ref name=\"P1\"/> It earned a record-breaking RMB 59.8&nbsp;million ($8.7&nbsp;million) from Thursday paid previews ($8&nbsp;million excluding online ticketing surcharges which now count as grosses), breaking its predecessor's former record of RMB 52.5&nbsp;million ($8.5&nbsp;million in 2015; $7.6&nbsp;million in 2017 exchange rates).<ref name=\"F\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/13/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-earns-28m-overseas-revs-engines-for-record-china-debut/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Earns $28M Overseas, Revs Engines For Record China Debut|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"OPD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fate-furious-smashes-single-day-record-994018|title=China Box Office: 'The Fate of the Furious' Smashes Single-Day Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> On Friday, the film was screened in approximately 158,000 screens, a new record for any film, breaking [[Warcraft (film)|''Warcraft'']]'s former 122,000 screen counts, and almost double the estimated 80,700 screen count of its predecessor.<ref name=\"CFI\">{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/on-screen-china-fate-of-the-furious-peels-out/|title=On Screen China: 'Fate of the Furious' Set To Peel Out|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> By Friday noon, it had already grossed $30&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/furious-8-overtakes-30-million-by-midday-in-china-opening-1202030643/|title='Furious 8' Revs Past $30 Million by Midday in China Opening|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Buoyed by positive word-of-mouth\u20149.4/10 user rating on mobile ticketing platform Maoyan, and 7.4/10 from reviews aggregator [[Douban]]\u2014and effective marketing campaign, it set a new record for the biggest single-day ever at the Chinese box office, including previews. This was achieved at 7 p.m. local time.<ref name=\"OPD\"/> In total, the film grossed an estimated RMB 452.8&nbsp;million ($65.8&nbsp;million) on its opening day, inclusive of previews and online ticketing surcharges, compared to the RMB 398 million ($57.8&nbsp;million) posted by its predecessor. It is the first film in Chinese history to register above RMB 400&nbsp;million ($58&nbsp;million) in a single day.<ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-china-openieg-records-1202030781/|title='Fate of the Furious' Speeds to Record-Breaking $65 Million Opening Day in China|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> Earning a total of RMB 1.323&nbsp;billion ($192.2&nbsp;million), according to Chinese sources and RMB 190 million, according to Universal, in its debut weekend, it set a new milestone for three-day opening weekend and overall the second-best debut ever behind only local pic ''[[The Mermaid (2016 film)|The Mermaid]]'', which had the benefit of four days of previews over the [[Chinese New Year|New Year]] period in February 2016. An estimated $14&nbsp;million came from 395 IMAX screens, the second-biggest-ever in the country, behind ''Warcraft''.<ref name=\"F58\"/> Its three-day debut alone made it the biggest Hollywood release of 2017 and the third-biggest overall. Factoring out online ticketing surcharges, the total comes to a slightly less-hefty RMB 1.245&nbsp;billion ($182.2&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"CFIOP\">{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/china-box-office-furious-8-paves-new-roads/|title=China Box Office: 'Furious 8' Paves New Roads|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> In just nine days, the film passed the historic RMB 2&nbsp;billion ($300&nbsp;million) and thereby became the biggest release of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/fate-of-the-furious-300-million-at-china-box-office-1202392915/|title='Fate of the Furious' Passes $300 Million at China Box Office|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 22, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> The film fell precipitously by 71.4% in its second weekend (from its $190&nbsp;million debut), earning RMB 374 million ($54.3&nbsp;million) for a massive 10-day total of RMB 2.19&nbsp;billion ($318&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fast-8-races-past-300m-chases-furious-7-all-time-record-996662|title=China Box Office: 'Fast 8' Races Past $300M, Chases 'Furious 7' for All-Time Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/china-box-office-smurfs-come-up-short-f8-remains/|title=China Box Office: Smurfs Come Up Short, F8 Remains #1|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 24, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> On April 30, it became the biggest Hollywood/foreign release of all time with RMB 2.44&nbsp;billion, surpassing its prequels former record of 2.41&nbsp;billion. However, in terms of US currency, ''The Fate of the Furious'' ($381&nbsp;million) is still behind ''Furious 7'' ($391&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"GotG\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fate-furious-overtakes-furious-7-become-biggest-hollywood-film-ever-998800|title=China Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Overtakes 'Furious 7' to Become Biggest Hollywood Film Ever|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> After three consecutive weeks of topping the charts, it slipped to fourth place after being dethroned by ''Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2'' from the top spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/china-box-office-guardians-2-beats-dangal-for-weekend-win-1202411713/|title=China Box Office: 'Guardians 2' Beats India's 'Dangal' For Weekend Win|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=May 7, 2017|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref> It has so far grossed a total of RMB 2.671&nbsp;billion ($392.8&nbsp;million) and is the country's second-biggest grosser ever, behind only ''The Mermaid'' at the time of its release.<ref name=\"JJ\"/>\n\nIn India, the film secured a release across approximately 1,600\u20131,800 screens (1,000\u20131,200 screens fewer than its predecessor). Like other Hollywood releases, it was released in both 2K projections and normal projections, and dubbed in local languages such as Hindi, Tamil and Telugu. It is the first international film to be dubbed into the [[Kannada]] language. Despite clashing with local film ''[[Begum Jaan]]'', analysts believe the two films will not affect each other's performance, as they appeal to distinct moviegoers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/furious-8-might-not-score-100-cr-in-india-begum-jaan-to-remain-unaffected/|title=Furious 8 Might Not Score 100 Cr in India; Begum Jaan To Remain Unaffected|first=Ahana |last=Bhattacharya|work=[[Koimoi]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/vidya-balans-begum-jaan-will-earn-rs-14-crore-over-the-first-weekend-while-dwayne-johnson-vin-diesels-the-fate-of-the-furious-will-rake-in-rs-35-crore/|title=Vidya Balan's Begum Jaan and Dwayne Johnson-Vin Diesel's The Fate of the Furious will rock the box office over the first weekend|author=Karan Shah|work=Hollywood Life|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-furious-8-first-hollywood-film-to-be-dubbed-in-kannada-2398669|title=Fate of the Furious is the first Hollywood film to be dubbed into Kannada|first=Subhash K. |last=Jha|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> Universal had high hopes in the territory, after ''Furious 7'' grossed an unprecedented $24.9&nbsp;million in 2015, and became the biggest foreign release ever in the country at the time of its release (now the second-biggest). The [[Central Board of Film Certification]] gave the film a UA rating (parental guidance suggested for children under 12), rather than an A for adults, after the studio agreed to cut several profanities (CBFC was willing to pass the film with an A certificate with no cuts but Universal wanted a UA certificate leading to the board censoring all profanities with few cuts).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/12/a-fast-and-furious-weekend-ahead-at-indian-cinemas/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=A Fast And Furious Weekend Ahead at Indian Cinemas|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> It earned around {{INRConvert|85.0|m}} net from Wednesday paid previews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/the-fate-of-the-furious-does-good-business-on-paid-previews-at-the-box-office-in-india/|title=The Fate of the Furious Does Good Business On Paid Previews at the Box Office in India|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> The following day it grossed {{INRConvert|225|m}}, including previews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/hollywood/fast-and-furious-8-box-office-collection-diesel-and-dwayne-johnson-film-4613405/|title=Fast and Furious 8 box office collection: Vin Diesel, Dwayne Johnson film earns Rs 22.50 crore in India|first=Samarpita |last=Das|work=[[The Indian Express]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> On its official opening day, it grossed {{INRConvert|161|m}} for a three-day total of {{INRConvert|386|m}}.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|number=853222969748869120|title=#Furious8 Wed previews 8.50 cr, Thu 14 cr, Fri 16.10 cr. Total: \u20b9 38.60 cr [note: Gross BO]. India biz. AWESOME! #TheFateOfTheFurious|authorlink=Taran Adarsh|last=Adarsh|first=Taran|date=April 15, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2018}}</ref> Earning a total of $10.7&nbsp;million, it set a new record for the biggest-ever foreign opening in the country, toppling its prequel's former record. As such, it is the first foreign film to open north of $10&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/16/gippy-grewal-and-tamil-stars-raghava-arya-and-rajkiran-battle-for-audiences-in-india/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Gippy Grewal And Tamil Stars Raghava, Arya And Rajkiran Battle For Audiences in India|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> Following its record breaking opening, it fell about 58% on its second weekend excluding previews, earning another $4&nbsp;million for a two-weekend total of over $17.4&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/23/raveena-tandon-rape-drama-maatr-sets-out-to-shock-and-succeeds/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Raveena Tandon Rape Drama 'Maatr' Sets Out To Shock \u2013 And Succeeds|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 24, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> With over $19.2&nbsp;million it is currently the biggest foreign release of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-fast-furious-8-becomes-highest-hollywood-grosser-2017-india-box-office-2/|title=Box Office: Fast and Furious 8 becomes the highest Hollywood grosser of 2017 at the India box office|author=Bollywood Hungama News Network|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=April 25, 2017}}</ref> However, in terms of net earnings\u2014which is the base for box office calculations in India\u2014the film was unable to break past the {{INRConvert|1|b}} mark, stalling at around {{INRConvert|856|m}}. Despite a record breaking opening, it lost significant amount of screen counts and audiences thereafter, partly due to the release of ''[[Baahubali 2: The Conclusion|Baahubali: The Conclusion]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-baahubali-2-conclusion-mania-engulfs-fast-furious-8-prevents-entering-100-cr-club-india-box-office/|title=Box Office: Baahubali 2 \u2013 The Conclusion mania engulfs Fast and Furious 8; prevents it from entering 100 cr. club at the India box office|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=May 6, 2017|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe biggest-earning markets are China ($392.8&nbsp;million), followed by Brazil ($41.8&nbsp;million), the UK and Ireland ($37.5&nbsp;million), Mexico ($36.8&nbsp;million) and Germany ($32.4&nbsp;million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=furious8.htm|title=The Fate of the Furious (2017) \u2013 International Box Office Results \u2013 Box Office Mojo|website=boxofficemojo.com|access-date=13 May 2018}}</ref> In Peru, it has become Universal's highest-grossing film ever.<ref name=\"Jap60\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-marvel-11-billion-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-international-china-box-office-weekend-1202086302/|title='Guardians 2' Notches $428M Global, Lifts MCU Past $11B; 'Furious 8' Tops $950M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|date=May 7, 2017|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref> With over $1&nbsp;billion in international receipts and representing a boffo 82% of the film's total worldwide gross, it is currently the seventh-biggest overseas earner behind ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', ''[[Titanic (1997 film)|Titanic]]'', ''Furious 7'', ''Star Wars: The Force Awakens'', and ''Jurassic World''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/?pagenum=1&sort=osgross&order=DESC&p=.htm|title=WORLDWIDE GROSSES|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' received mixed reviews.<ref name=\"reviews1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/love-sex/critics-give-mixed-reviews-to-the-fate-of-the-furious/vp-BBzQxFI |title=Critics Give Mixed Reviews To 'The Fate of the Furious'|work=MSN News|publisher=[[MSN]]|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"reviews2\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-reviews-round-up-1202027165/ |title=Fate of the Furious' Reviews: What the Critics Are Saying|work=Variety|accessdate=April 16, 2017|date=April 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Dickey|first1=Josh|title=Critics can't agree if 'Fate of the Furious' is fantastic or a pile of garbage|url=http://mashable.com/2017/04/09/fate-furious-8-reviews-movies-roundup/|accessdate=January 14, 2018|work=[[Mashable]]|date=April 10, 2017}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 67% based on 301 reviews, and an [[average rating]] of 6.13/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''The Fate of the Furious'' opens a new chapter in the franchise, fueled by the same infectious cast chemistry and over-the-top action fans have come to expect.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_fate_of_the_furious |title=The Fate of the Furious (2017) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score 56 out of 100, based on 45 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-fate-of-the-furious |title=The Fate of the Furious Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale,<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite tweet|user=CinemaScore |number=853100097802055680 |title=Congratulations on your A #cinemascore grade! @KristoferHivju @Kurtrussell @Nealmoritz #FateandtheFurious |author=[[CinemaScore]] |date=April 14, 2017 |accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it an 88% overall positive score and a 71% \"definite recommend.\"<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nMike Ryan of ''[[Uproxx]]'' gave the film a positive review, writing: \"This isn't my favorite of the series\u2014that's still ''[[Furious 7]]'' (it's hard to top those jumps from skyscraper to skyscraper, but this is a worthy entry). These movies know what they are. These movies know they are fun. These are fun movies!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/movies/the-fate-of-the-furious-review/ |title='The Fate of the Furious': This Time They Fight A Submarine |website=[[Uproxx]] |date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref> [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', in his positive review of the film, wrote: \"Most franchises, after eight films, are feeling a twinge of exhaustion, but this one has achieved a level of success\u2014and perpetual kinetic creative energy\u2014that's a testament to its commercial/cultural/demographic resonance.\" He also wrote, \"If this series, over the last 16 years, has taught us anything, it's that just when you think it's about to run out of gas, it gets outfitted with an even more elaborate fuel-injection system.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202026947/|title=Film Review: 'The Fate of the Furious' |date=April 9, 2017|last=Gleiberman |first=Owen|authorlink=Owen Gleiberman|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\nDavid Ehrlich of [[IndieWire]] gave the film a C\u2212 and called it the worst entry of the franchise, saying: \"As much a mess of conflicting tones and styles as it is of locations, this setpiece\u2014like the rest of Gray's movie\u2014feels like a heap of random parts that were thrown together in the hopes that fate might somehow weld them into a roadworthy vehicle. But it's not all groundbreaking.\"<ref>{{cite web|first=David |last=Ehrlich |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-vin-diesel-the-rock-charlize-theron-worst-fast-and-furious-movie-1201803492/ |title='The Fate of the Furious' Review: Vin Diesel's Family Becomes Dysfunctional in Worst 'Fast and Furious' Ever |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=April 9, 2017 |accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref> J. R. Kinnard of ''[[PopMatters]]'' magazine gave a lukewarm review, writing: \"It's unlikely that devotees will consider ''The Fate of the Furious'' one of the stronger entries in the series. Still, the filmmakers and actors are clearly dedicated to making a quality product, avoiding the complacency that often plagues action sequels.\"<ref name=PM>{{cite web|work=[[PopMatters]]|last=Kinnard |first=J.R.|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/the-fate-of-the-furious-f-gary-gray-van-disel-meets-crocodile/|title='The Fate of the Furious' Dom (Vin Diesel) Meets the Crocodile|date=April 13, 2017}}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film 2 out of 4 stars, saying: \"Moments after Dom has gone rogue and apparently wants to kill them, they're making jokes. As they're racing through the streets of New York City or skidding along the ice in Russia, killing bad guys and narrowly avoiding getting killed themselves, they're crackin' wise. Even within this ludicrous universe, it's jarring to hear these supposedly smart folks, who refer to themselves as 'family,' acting like idiots who don't seem to care if they live or die, or if their friends survive.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/overlong-idiotic-fate-of-the-furious-drags-down-the-franchise/ |title=Overlong, idiotic 'Fate of the Furious' drags down the franchise |newspaper=[[Chicago Sun-Times]] | authorlink=Richard Roeper| author=Roeper, Richard| date=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nProfessor of international [[political economy]] Richard E. Feinberg has commented on the political significance of the film's opening setting of [[Havana]] in the context of shifting [[Cuba\u2013United States relations|U.S.\u2013Cuban relations]], calling the eighth instalment, \"Hollywood's love letter to Havana\".<ref name=\"Feinberg\">{{cite web|url=https://cubacounterpoints.com/archives/5368|title=Fast and Furious 8: Hollywood's Love Letter to Havana|last=Feinberg|first=Richard E.|date=May 4, 2017|website=cubacounterpoints.com|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> He writes, \"In the Cuban sequence's dramatic climax, Dom wins his hard-fought one-mile race (\"a Cuban mile\") against a tough local competitor, by a nose. The loser is gracious: 'You won my car and you earned my respect,' he admits to the FF hero. Dom's response is equally magnanimous: 'Keep your car, your respect is good enough for me.' In this instance, FF8 captures the essence of the relations between the United States and Cuba: it's all about mutual respect.\"<ref name=\"Feinberg\" />\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"6\"| [[2017 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie - Action|Choice Movie: Action]]\n!\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Choice Movie Actor: Action\n| [[Vin Diesel]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Actress: Action\n| [[Michelle Rodriguez]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain|Choice Movie: Villain]]\n| [[Charlize Theron]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie: Ship\n| Michelle Rodriguez and Vin Diesel\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[44th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Action or Adventure Film|Best Action or Adventure Film]]\n| ''The Fate of the Furious''\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|title='Black Panther,' 'Walking Dead' Rule Saturn Awards Nominations|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 15, 2018|accessdate=March 15, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6xwc1azco?url=http://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|archivedate=March 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]\n| [[Christian Wagner]] and [[Paul Rubell]]\n|}\n\n== Sequel ==\n{{Main|F9 (film)}}\nOn February 3, 2016, Universal Pictures set initial release dates for the two remaining films in the franchise, with the first, ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]'', given an initial release date of April 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rahman|first=Abid|title=Universal Sets Dates for 'Fast & Furious' Parts 9 and 10|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-furious-8-9-10-861585|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 3, 2016 |accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> However, on October 4, 2017, the release date was pushed back to April 10, 2020, to accommodate for the spin-off film ''[[Hobbs & Shaw]]'',<ref name=\"Sequels\">{{cite web|last=Dornbush|first=Jonathon|title=FAST AND FURIOUS 9 RELEASE DATE DELAYED|url=http://m.ign.com/articles/2017/10/04/fast-and-furious-9-release-date-delayed|work=[[IGN]]|date=October 4, 2017 |accessdate=October 5, 2017}}</ref> which was released on August 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|title='Fast & Furious' Spinoff With Dwayne Johnson & Jason Statham Shifts to August 2019|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/dwayne-johnson-jason-statham-fast-furious-spin-off-summer-2019-release-1202182987/|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 9, 2018|accessdate=May 15, 2018}}</ref> The announcement of the spin-off provoked a response on [[Instagram]] by [[Tyrese Gibson]], criticizing [[Dwayne Johnson]] and [[Seven Bucks Productions]] co-creator Hiram Garcia (who served as producers for the spin-off) for causing the ninth film to be delayed for another year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast & Furious: The Rock And Jason Statham Spin-Off Coming In 2019|url=https://whatculture.com/film/fast-furious-the-rock-and-jason-statham-spin-off-coming-in-2019|work=WhatCulture.com|date=October 6, 2017|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref> ''F9'' was then pushed back to April 2, 2021 as a result of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=N}}\n \n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{official website|http://www.fastandfurious.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|4630562}}\n* {{AllMovie title|643403}}\n\n{{The Fast and the Furious}}\n{{F. Gary Gray}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fate of the Furious, The}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s chase films]]\n[[Category:2010s heist films]]\n[[Category:2010s road movies]]\n[[Category:2010s sequel films]]\n[[Category:Action films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American action thriller films]]\n[[Category:American chase films]]\n[[Category:Original Film films]]\n[[Category:American heist films]]\n[[Category:American road movies]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:China Film Group Corporation films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Fast & Furious]]\n[[Category:Films about automobiles]]\n[[Category:Films about nuclear war and weapons]]\n[[Category:Films about terrorism]]\n[[Category:Films directed by F. Gary Gray]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Neal H. Moritz]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Brian Tyler]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Films set in Havana]]\n[[Category:Films set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Films set on airplanes]]\n[[Category:Films set in prison]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Arctic]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Havana]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Iceland]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Cleveland]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:One Race Films films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Chris Morgan]]\n[[Category:Sequel films]]\n[[Category:Submarine films]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 American action film by F. Gary Gray}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Fate of the Furious\n| image          = The Fate of The Furious Theatrical Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[F. Gary Gray]]\n| producer       = {{Plain list |\n* [[Neal H. Moritz]]\n* [[Vin Diesel]]\n* Michael Fottrell\n* [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]]<!--PER CREDITS-->\n}}\n| writer         = Chris Morgan\n| based on       = {{Based on|[[List of The Fast and the Furious characters|Characters]]|[[Gary Scott Thompson]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plain list |\n* Vin Diesel <!-- Do not add link here per MOS:REPEATLINK as Diesel is already linked above. -->\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n* [[Jason Statham]]\n* [[Michelle Rodriguez]]\n* [[Tyrese Gibson]]\n* [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]]\n* [[Scott Eastwood]]\n* [[Nathalie Emmanuel]]\n* [[Elsa Pataky]]\n* [[Kurt Russell]]\n* [[Charlize Theron]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Brian Tyler]]\n| cinematography = [[Stephen F. Windon]]\n| editing        = {{Unbulleted list|[[Christian Wagner]]|[[Paul Rubell]]}}\n| studio         = {{Unbulleted list|[[Original Film]]|[[One Race Films]] |[[China Film Group Corporation|China Film]]}}\n| distributor    = [[Universal Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2017|4|4|[[Berlin]]|2017|4|14|United States}}\n| runtime        = {{Plain list |\n* 136 minutes (theatrical release)\n* 148 minutes (director's cut)\n}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $250 million<ref name=\"2017FFS\">{{Cite journal |date= August 2018 |title= 2017 Feature Film Study |url= https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/2017_film_study_v3-WEB.pdf |journal= FilmL.A. Feature Film Study |page= 25 |accessdate= August 9, 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"DEADopen\" />\n| gross          = $1.236&nbsp;billion<ref>{{cite web |title= The Fate of the Furious (14 April 2017) |work= [[Boxoffice (magazine)|Boxoffice]] |url= http://pro.boxoffice.com/movie/29210/the-fate-of-the-furious |accessdate= May 7, 2018 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Fate of the Furious''''' (alternatively known as '''''F8''''' and '''''Fast & Furious 8''''') is a 2017 American [[action film]] directed by [[F. Gary Gray]] and written by [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]]. A sequel to 2015's ''[[Furious 7]]'', it is the eighth installment in the ''[[Fast & Furious]]'' franchise and stars [[Vin Diesel]], [[Dwayne Johnson]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Michelle Rodriguez]], [[Tyrese Gibson]], [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]], [[Scott Eastwood]], [[Nathalie Emmanuel]], [[Elsa Pataky]], [[Kurt Russell]] and [[Charlize Theron]]. ''The Fate of the Furious'' follows [[Dominic Toretto]] (Diesel), who has settled down with his wife [[Letty Ortiz]] (Rodriguez), until [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] Cipher (Theron) coerces him into working for her and turns him against his team, forcing them to find Dom and take down Cipher.\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' marks the first installment in the franchise since ''[[The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift]]'' (2006) not to feature [[Paul Walker]], who died on November 30, 2013 in a [[single-vehicle crash]] while the filming of ''Furious 7'' was still in progress<ref>{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Hazel|title=Paul Walker died due to road accident|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3020710/Death-Fast-Furious-star-Paul-Walker-solely-actions-driver-friend-Porsche-claims-lawsuit.html|work=[[Daily Mail]]|date=April 1, 2015|accessdate=May 25, 2015}}</ref> Script rewrites to the seventh installment after Walker's death were intended to complete the story arc for his character, [[Brian O'Conner]].\n\nPlans for an eighth installment were first announced in March 2015 when Diesel appeared on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'' and announced that the film would be set in New York City. Preparations for the film began immediately after the release of ''Furious 7'', with Diesel, Morgan, and producer [[Neal H. Moritz]] re-signing. After setting an initial release date in the same month, casting took place between April and June 2015. In October 2015, Gray was announced to direct the film in the place of [[James Wan]], who had directed the previous installment. [[Principal photography]] began in March 2016 in locations such as [[M\u00fdvatn]], [[Havana]], [[Atlanta]], [[Cleveland]], and New York City, continuing the franchise's tradition of filming in exotic locations around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Where was The Fate of the Furious filmed?|url=http://www.atlasofwonders.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-furious-filming-locations.html|work=Atlas of Wonders|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' premiered in [[Berlin]] on April 4, 2017 and was theatrically released in conventional and [[IMAX]] theaters in the United States on April 14, 2017 while also playing in [[3D film|3D]], [[IMAX 3D]], and [[4DX]] internationally. The film received mixed reviews from critics, many of whom praised the performances and action sequences, but criticized the storyline. The film grossed over $1.2&nbsp;billion worldwide, making it the thirtieth film (and the second in the franchise, after ''Furious 7'') to gross over $1&nbsp;billion, the [[2017 in film#Highest grossing films|third-highest-grossing film of 2017]] and the [[List of highest-grossing films|nineteenth highest-grossing film of all time]]. It also grossed $541.9&nbsp;million worldwide during its opening weekend, which made it the [[list of highest-grossing openings for films|highest-grossing worldwide opening of all time]] until the release of ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' the following year. \n\nA sequel, ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]'', is scheduled to be released on April 2, 2021.\n\n== Plot ==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for feature-length films should be between 400 and 700 words. -->\nFollowing the defeat of [[Deckard Shaw]] and Mose Jakande,{{refn|group=N|As depicted in the 2015 film ''[[Furious 7]]''.}} [[Dominic Toretto|Dominic \"Dom\" Toretto]] and Letty Ortiz are on their honeymoon in [[Havana]] when Dom's cousin Fernando gets in trouble owing money to local racer Raldo. Sensing Raldo is a [[loan shark]], Dom challenges Raldo to a race, pitting Fernando's reworked car against Raldo's, and wagering his own Third Generation [[Chevrolet Impala]]. After narrowly winning the race, Dom allows Raldo to keep his car, earning his respect, and instead leaves his cousin with his car.\n\nThe next day, Dom is approached by the elusive [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] Cipher who coerces him into working for her by showing him an unseen photo. Shortly afterwards, Dom and his team, comprising Letty, Roman Pearce, Tej Parker, and Ramsey, are recruited by [[Diplomatic Security Service]] (DSS) agent Luke Hobbs to help him retrieve an [[Electromagnetic pulse|EMP device]] from a military outpost in [[Berlin]]. During the getaway, Dom goes rogue, forcing Hobbs off the road and stealing the device for Cipher. Hobbs is arrested and locked up in the same high-security prison in which he helped imprison Shaw. After Shaw and Hobbs both escape the prison, they are recruited by intelligence operative [[List of The Fast and the Furious characters#Mr. Nobody|Mr. Nobody]] and his prot\u00e9g\u00e9 to help the team find Dom and capture Cipher. Shaw reveals that Cipher had hired his brother Owen to steal the Nightshade device and Mose Jakande to steal God's Eye, Ramsey's software program. The team tracks Dom and Cipher to their very location just as the latter two attack the base, causing injuries to the team, and stealing God's Eye. Roman suggests bringing [[Brian O'Conner|Brian]] in to help them, but Letty rejects the idea as they agreed not to bring him & Mia into any more missions for the sake of their children.\n\nWhen Dom questions Cipher's motives, she reveals that she has been holding hostage Dom's ex-lover and DSS agent Elena Neves\u2014as well as their son, of whose existence Dom was previously unaware. Elena tells Dom that she wanted him to decide the child's first name, having already given him the middle name Marcos.\n\nIn New York City, Cipher sends Dom to retrieve a [[nuclear football]] held by the [[Ministry of Defense (Russia)|Russian Minister of Defense]]. Prior to the theft, Dom briefly evades Cipher\u2014with the help of Raldo\u2014and persuades Shaw's mother, Magdalene Shaw, to help him. Cipher hacks into the electronics systems of a large number of cars, causing them to disable the convoy so that Dom can take the football. The team intercepts Dom, but Dom escapes, shooting and apparently killing Shaw in the process. Letty catches up to Dom, but is ambushed and nearly killed by Cipher's enforcer, Connor Rhodes, before Dom rescues her. In retaliation, Cipher has Rhodes execute Elena in front of a helpless Dom.\n\nDom infiltrates a base in Russia to use the EMP device to disable their security and then to disable a [[nuclear submarine]], enabling Cipher to hijack it and attempt to use its arsenal to trigger a nuclear war. They are once again intercepted by the team, who attempt to shut down the sub, and then drive out toward the gates that would prevent the sub from leaving into open waters. Meanwhile, Shaw, whose death was faked, teams up with Owen, and at Magdalene's behest, infiltrates Cipher's plane to rescue Dom's son. Once Shaw reports that the child is safe, Dom turns on Cipher and kills Rhodes, before rejoining his team. Infuriated, Cipher fires an [[infrared homing]] missile at Dom, but he breaks away from his team and maneuvers around it, causing the missile to hit the submarine instead. The team quickly forms a vehicular blockade around Dom, shielding him from the ensuing explosion. Shaw reaches the front of the plane and confronts Cipher, who jumps from the plane with a parachute.\n\nMr. Nobody and his prot\u00e9g\u00e9 visit Dom and his team in New York City to report that Cipher is still at large in [[Athens]]. Hobbs is offered his DSS job back, but he declines in order to spend more time with his daughter. Shaw delivers Dom his son, putting his differences aside with Dom and Hobbs. \n\nDom names his son Brian, after his friend and brother-in-law [[Brian O'Conner]], and celebrates with his friends.\n\n==Cast==\n{{details|topic=the characters|List of Fast & Furious characters}}\n* [[Vin Diesel]] as [[Dominic Toretto]], a former criminal and professional street racer who has retired and settled down with his wife, Letty. He is [[coerced]] by Cipher to work against his team.\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]] as [[Luke Hobbs]], a [[Diplomatic Security Service]] (DSS) agent who allied with Dom and his team following their outings in [[Rio de Janeiro]] and Europe.\n* [[Jason Statham]] as [[Deckard Shaw]], a rogue British Special Forces assassin who was imprisoned by Hobbs and the DSS after his defeat in Los Angeles, who serves as an ally to help Dom's team take down Cipher.\n* [[Michelle Rodriguez]] as [[Letty Ortiz]], Dom's wife and a former professional street racer.\n* [[Tyrese Gibson]] as [[Roman Pearce]], a former criminal from [[Barstow, California|Barstow]] and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Ludacris|Chris \"Ludacris\" Bridges]] as [[Tej Parker]], a mechanic from Miami and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Scott Eastwood]] as Eric Reisner / Little Nobody,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/2017/4/9/15218064/fast-and-furious-8-fate-of-the-furious-review|title=Fast and Furious 8: 5 things to know about The Fate of the Furious|last=Abad-Santos |first=Alex|date=April 11, 2017|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/fate-of-the-furious-ending-post-credit-scene|title=What the Ending of 'The Fate of the Furious' Could Mean for the 'Fast' Franchise|first=Dan|last=Jackson|date=April 18, 2017|website=[[Thrillist]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> a law enforcement agent working under Mr. Nobody.\n* [[Nathalie Emmanuel]] as Ramsey, a computer [[Hacktivism|hacktivist]] and a member of Dom's team.\n* [[Elsa Pataky]] as Elena Neves, the mother of Dom's child and a former Rio de Janeiro police officer who moved to the United States to become Hobbs' new partner at the DSS.\n* [[Kurt Russell]] as Mr. Nobody,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagonow.com/seven-gunn-says/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-ff8/|title=The Fate of the Furious Review: FF8|author=Seven Gunn Says|date=April 14, 2017|website=[[ChicagoNow]]|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> an intelligence operative and the leader of a covert ops team which previously aided Dom and his team in taking down Deckard in [[Abu Dhabi]].\n* [[Charlize Theron]] as Cipher, a criminal mastermind and [[Cyberterrorism|cyberterrorist]] who coerces Dom into working against his team by holding Elena and their son hostage.\n\n[[Tego Calder\u00f3n]] and [[Don Omar]] reprise their respective roles as Tego Leo and Rico Santos, former members of Dom's team, from previous films. [[Kristofer Hivju]] portrays Connor Rhodes, Cipher's enforcer and right-hand man, and [[Patrick St. Esprit]] appears as DS Allen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.militarypress.com/the-fate-of-the-furious-revs-up-the-engines-again/|title='The Fate of the Furious' revs up the engines again|last=Jacquin|first=Jeri|date=April 14, 2017|website=MilitaryPress|accessdate=November 7, 2017}}</ref> [[Luke Evans (actor)|Luke Evans]] reprises his role from ''[[Fast & Furious 6]]'' (2013) and ''[[Furious 7]]'' (2015) as Owen Shaw, Deckard's younger brother and a former [[Special Air Service]] (SAS) soldier who formerly opposed Dom's team in Europe, and who helps his brother in rescuing Dom's son. [[Helen Mirren]] makes an uncredited [[cameo appearance]] as Magdalene Shaw, the mother of Deckard and Owen Shaw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1635570/how-helen-mirren-ended-up-in-the-fate-of-the-furious-according-to-vin-diesel|title=How Helen Mirren Ended Up in the Fate of the Furious, According To Vin Diesel|last=Wakeman|first=Gregory|date=March 14, 2017|website=CinemaBlend|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> Celestino Cornielle portrays Raldo, a street racer whose respect Dom earns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiddenremote.com/2017/04/30/celestino-cornielle-road-fate-furious/|title=Celestino Cornielle On His Road To \u2018The Fate Of The Furious\u2019|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nFollowing the release of ''[[Furious 7]]'' (2015), [[Vin Diesel]] said regarding a possible sequel:\n\n{{quote|text=I was trying to keep it close to the vest throughout the release. [[Paul Walker]] used to say that [an eighth film] was guaranteed. And in some ways, when your brother guarantees something, you sometimes feel like you have to make sure it comes to pass ... so if fate has it, then you'll get this when you hear about it. [''Furious 7''] was for Paul, [the eighth film] is from Paul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/2015/04/13/vin-diesel-says-furious-7-was-for-paul-and-8-will-be-from-paul/|title=Vin Diesel Says Furious 7 Was For Paul And 8 Will Be From Paul|author=Joe Comicbook|work=Comicbook.com}}</ref>|sign=|source=}}\n\n{{quote box|width=27%|align=right|quote=We're trying to do what we always do, which is try to come at it from a character point of view and figure out where the characters would go from here. I think the thing that's made ''[[The Fast and the Furious]]'' special is obviously we have incredible action and so on. But the thing that people really relate to the most is the characters. We're lucky that we have a lot of great characters. Unfortunately, we don't have Paul [Walker] anymore. His character... has moved on. But we feel like there's a lot still to be mined. That's where we're starting. We're really talking about the characters, where they all sit right now. It's a huge challenge.|source=\u2014[[Neal H. Moritz]], ''The Fast and the Furious'' franchise producer<ref name=\"Characters\">{{cite web|last=Yaniz|first=Robert, Jr.|title='Furious 8' Producer Discusses Continuing Without Paul Walker|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-furious-8-paul-walker/|work=Screen Rant|date=July 22, 2015|accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref>}}\n\nDiesel further hinted at an eighth film on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'' when he stated that [[Kurt Russell]]'s character would span multiple films. He also stated that the next film would take place in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/fast-and-furious-8-setting-kurt-russell/|title=Vin Diesel Teases Fast and Furious 8 Setting in New York|work=Slashfilm|date=March 31, 2015|accessdate=March 31, 2015}}</ref> [[Chris Morgan (writer)|Chris Morgan]] returned to write his sixth script in the franchise, while [[Neal H. Moritz]] returned to produce. Moritz later stated, \"[The story] is going to have to be something enticing for all of us. It has to be as good as or better [than ''Furious 7'']\".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-8-nowhere-starting-line-787045 | title='Fast 8' Nowhere Near Starting Line | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=April 8, 2015 | accessdate=April 21, 2015 | first1=Rebecca |last1=Ford |first2=Borys |last2=Kit}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2015 [[CinemaCon]] in [[Las Vegas]], Diesel announced the film for an April 14, 2017 release date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/furious-8-gets-2017-release-791103|title='Furious 8' Gets 2017 Release Date|first=Rebecca |last=Ford|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=April 24, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/furious-8-to-debut-april-14-2017-1201478792/|title='Furious 8' to Debut April 14, 2017|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=April 24, 2015}}</ref> On August 16, 2015, at the [[2015 Teen Choice Awards]] (where ''Furious 7'' received the award for [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie - Action|Choice Movie \u2013 Action]] and Walker received the award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Action), Diesel gave the film the initial title ''Fast 8''.<ref>{{cite web|last=O'Connell|first=Sean|title=Vin Diesel Just Dropped The Name of the Next Fast & Furious Movie|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Vin-Diesel-Just-Dropped-Name-Next-Fast-Furious-Movie-77617.html|work=Cinema Blend|date=August 17, 2015|accessdate=August 20, 2015}}</ref> In September 2015, Diesel stated that the script had almost been completed,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Busch|first1=Anita|title=Will Vin Diesel Direct 'Furious 8'?|url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/vin-diesel-furious-8-director-universal-1201558992/|accessdate=October 7, 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=October 1, 2015}}</ref> and expressed interest in [[Rob Cohen]], who directed the [[The Fast and the Furious (2001 film)|first film]], to direct the eighth installment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vin Diesel Wants Rob Cohen to Direct Furious 8|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/618557-vin-diesel-wants-rob-cohen-to-direct-furious-8|accessdate=October 4, 2015|work=comingsoon.net|date=October 1, 2015}}</ref> On October 14, 2015, Diesel announced on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' that ''[[Straight Outta Compton (film)|Straight Outta Compton]]'' director [[F. Gary Gray]] would direct the film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Silver|first=Stephen|title=Fast and Furious 8: Vin Diesel Re-Confirms New York Setting|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-and-furious-8-new-york-setting-vin-diesel/|work=Screen Rant|date=October 16, 2015|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=VIDEO: Vin Diesel Reveals Setting & Director for 'FAST 8' on Tonight Show|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/VIDEO-Vin-Diesel-Reveals-Setting-Director-for-FAST-8-on-Tonight-Show-20151015|work=BWW TV World|date=October 15, 2015|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, Moritz said that Walker's character, Brian O'Conner, would not appear in the film, following the use of [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] in the previous film after Walker died in a [[single-vehicle accident]] on November 30, 2013, with Moritz stating that his character had \"moved on\".<ref name=\"Characters\"/> It had previously been reported that Paul's younger brother, [[Cody Walker (actor)|Cody Walker]], would either join the cast in a new role,<ref>{{cite web|last=Jordan|first=Shane|title='Fast and Furious 8' Paul Walker Brother Cody Cast in New Role?|url=http://www.classicalite.com/articles/23888/20150613/fast-furious-8-paul-walker-brother-cody-cast-new-role.htm|work=Classicalite|date=June 13, 2015|accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref> or replace his older brother in the role of O'Conner;<ref>{{cite web|last=Monalo|first=Komfie|title=Fast and Furious 8 Release Date, Cast: Will Cody Walker Replace Paul Walker (Brian O'Conner)?|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/56362/20150702/fast-furious-8-release-date-cast-will-cody-walker-replace-paul-brian-oconnor.htm|work=Gospel Herald|date=July 2, 2013|accessdate=July 3, 2015}}</ref> however, it was later announced that the character will not return to the franchise.<ref>{{cite web|last=Agpalo|first=Jaja|title='Fast and Furious 8' Release Date & Cast: Cody Walker Not Returning; Will The Plot Still Include Paul Walker? Plus, Other Details We Know [VIDEO]|url=http://www.foodworldnews.com/articles/52975/20151112/fast-furious-8-release-date-cast-cody-walker-returning-will.htm|work=Food World News|date=November 12, 2015|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref> Moritz also said that the film would shift the focus of the franchise from a series of [[heist film]]s to a [[Spy film|spy caper]], following a similar change in focus from [[street racing]] in ''[[Fast Five]]'' (2011).<ref>{{cite web|last=Sokol|first=Tony|title=Fast & Furious 8 Movie Casting News: 'Fast and Furious 8' Will Begin New Trilogy As Soon As They Find A Director, Which Hinges On Finding Screenplay|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/226898/20150803/fast-furious-8-movie-casting-news-will-begin-new-trilogy.htm|work=KpopStarz|date=August 3, 2015|accessdate=August 4, 2015}}</ref> In December 2016, the film was retitled ''The Fate of the Furious''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-8-retitled-fate-of-the-furious-trailer-teaser-arrives/|title=Fast 8 Retitled Fate of the Furious; Trailer Teaser Arrives|work=Screen Rant|date=December 9, 2016|accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nDiesel, Russell and [[Michelle Rodriguez]] were the first to confirm their involvement in the film, and [[Tyrese Gibson]] and [[Ludacris|Chris Bridges]] both confirmed their return soon after.<ref>{{cite web|last=Das|first=Chandan|title='Fast & Furious 8' Cast News, Release Date: Eva Mendes As Undercover Agent Monica Fuentes|url=http://www.breathecast.com/articles/fast-furious-8-cast-news-and-release-date-eva-mendes-to-return-as-undercover-agent-monica-29152/|work=BreatheCast|date=June 29, 2015|accessdate=July 2, 2015}}</ref> [[Lucas Black]] had signed on to reprise his role from ''[[The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift]]'' as Sean Boswell for ''Furious 7'', and two more instalments in September 2013, though he did not appear in ''Fate''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Eisenberg|first=Eric|title=Lucas Black Signs On For Fast & Furious 7, 8 And 9|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Lucas-Black-Signs-Fast-Furious-7-8-9-39448.html|work=Cinema Blend|date=September 16, 2013|accessdate=July 2, 2015}}</ref> In May 2015, [[Dwayne Johnson]] confirmed his involvement in the film, additionally hinting at a possible spin-off film involving his character, Luke Hobbs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast & Furious 8: Dwayne Johnson confirms his return|url=http://www.msn.com/en-gb/entertainment/story/fast-and-furious-8-dwayne-johnson-confirms-his-return/ar-BBjWpJw?ocid=MSNCOEO|publisher=[[MSN]]|date=May 19, 2015|accessdate=June 25, 2015}}</ref> [[Jason Statham]] also confirmed his return.<ref>{{cite web|last=Brew|first=Simon|title=Exclusive: Jason Statham on Crank 3 and Fast & Furious 8|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/jason-statham/35542/exclusive-jason-statham-on-crank-3-and-fast-furious-8|work=[[Den of Geek]]|date=May 28, 2015|accessdate=June 25, 2015}}</ref> In April 2016, [[Charlize Theron]] and [[Kristofer Hivju]] were confirmed as additions to the cast, in villainous roles,<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin|title=Charlize Theron Joins 'Fast 8'|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/charlize-theron-fast-8-vin-diesel-1201743898/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 7, 2016|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Morrison|first=Sara|title=Kristofer Hivju cast in 'Fast & Furious 8'|url=http://www.hitfix.com/news/kristofer-hivju-cast-in-fast-furious-8|work=Hitfix|date=April 7, 2016|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref> while [[Scott Eastwood]] also joined the film as a law enforcement agent.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/fast-8-new-character-scott-eastwood-starring-1201735483/ | title='Fast 8' Creates New Character; Scott Eastwood To Star | work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]| date=April 11, 2016 | accessdate=April 13, 2016 | author=Mike Fleming Jr}}</ref> On May 17, 2016, Diesel posted a photo on his [[Instagram]] page of himself and [[Elsa Pataky]] on set, indicating that she had also returned for the film,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BFfMtGHmPo2/|title=Instagram photo by Vin Diesel \u2022 May 17, 2016 at 12:00&nbsp;am UTC|work=[[Instagram]]|date=May 17, 2016|accessdate=May 18, 2016}}</ref> and was followed two days later by a video on set with [[Nathalie Emmanuel]], who also starred in the previous film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BFkCMgTmPrA/|title=Instagram video by Vin Diesel \u2022 May 18, 2016 at 9:05&nbsp;pm UTC|work=[[Instagram]]|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 20, 2016}}</ref> In June 2016, [[Helen Mirren]] announced in an interview with ''Elle'' that she would appear in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/movies-tv/news/a37050/helen-mirren-interview/|title=Helen Mirren On Eye in the Sky, and (Exclusive!) the Huge Franchise She'll Star in Next|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=June 15, 2016}}</ref> In July 2016, [[Don Omar]] tweeted that he and [[Tego Calderon]] would return to the franchise for the eighth picture.<ref>{{cite tweet |author= DON OMAR aka KONG  |user= DONOMAR|number= 752522004373307392 |date= July 11, 2016 |title= Is time to work! We are back! @TEGOCALDERON @DONOMAR #LosBandoleros #NewMusicMonday #FF8 |access-date= December 12, 2016}}</ref> During an interview with [[Chris Mannix]] on July 21, 2016, Lucas Black confirmed he would not appear in the eighth instalment, due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://audioboom.com/posts/4846469-the-chris-mannix-show-lucas-black|title=The Chris Mannix Show \u2013 Lucas Black|date=July 21, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nIn keeping with the franchise's penchant for filming in \"exotic\" locations, such as [[Dubai]] and [[Rio de Janeiro]], in January 2016 it was announced that Universal was seeking approval from the [[Federal government of the United States|United States]] and [[Politics of Cuba|Cuban governments]] to shoot part of the film in [[Cuba]].<ref name=\"Cuba\">{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|last2=Kroll|first2=Justin|title='Fast and Furious 8' Wants to Shoot in Cuba (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/fast-and-furious-8-wants-to-shoot-in-cuba-exclusive-1201672531/|work=Variety|date=January 6, 2016|access-date=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ford|first1=Rebecca|last2=Kit|first2=Borys|title='Fast and Furious 8' to Shoot in Cuba (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-furious-8-shoot-cuba-850559|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=January 6, 2016}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] began on March 14, 2016, in [[M\u00fdvatn]], [[Iceland]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast 8 scenes filmed at M\u00fdvatn|url=http://icelandmonitor.mbl.is/news/culture_and_living/2016/02/22/fast_8_scenes_filmed_at_myvatn/|work=Iceland Monitor|date=February 22, 2016|access-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The car stars of Fast and the Furious 8|url=http://icelandmonitor.mbl.is/news/culture_and_living/2016/03/07/the_car_stars_of_fast_and_the_furious_8/|work=Iceland Monitor|date=March 7, 2016|access-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref> where strong winds sent a plastic iceberg prop flying into a paddock. The prop struck two horses: one was wounded and the other mortally injured; it was later euthanized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/03/14/fast-and-furious-8-horse-iceberg-dead/|title='Fast & Furious 8' Horse Killed By Flying 'Iceberg'|work=[[TMZ.com]]|date=March 14, 2016|access-date=March 16, 2016}}</ref> In late April, filming began in Cuba's capital city, [[Havana]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vin Diesel and Michelle Rodriguez are already in Havana!|url=http://www.cubaheadlines.com/2016-04-20-p13-vin-diesel-and-michelle-rodriguez-are-already-in-havana.html|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=Cuba Headlines|date=April 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fast and Furious Filming in Cuba|url=http://www.havanatimes.org/?p=118318|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=Havana Times.org|date=April 24, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Cruz|first1=Janna Dela|title='Fast and Furious 8' production update: The Rock prepares for return, Michelle Rodriguez, Vin Diesel arrive in Cuba for filming {{!}} Christian News on Christian Today|url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/fast.and.furious.8.production.update.the.rock.prepares.for.return.michelle.rodriguez.vin.diesel.arrive.in.cuba.for.filming/84804.htm|access-date=April 27, 2016|work=christiantoday.com|date=April 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-f-gary-gray-interview-cuba-embargo|title=Is Fate of the Furious's \"Cuban Mile\" Real?|first=Laura|last=Bradley|website=Vanity Fair|access-date=October 25, 2017}}</ref> In May, filming also took place in [[Cleveland]], Ohio.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Morona|first1=Joey|title='Fast & Furious 8' to shoot scenes in Cleveland|url=http://www.cleveland.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2016/03/fast_furious_8_cleveland.html|access-date=April 10, 2016|work=The Plain Dealer|date=March 30, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Fong|first1=Marvin|title=Filming for 'Fast 8' begins in Cleveland (photos)|url=http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2016/05/filming_for_fast_8_begins_in_c.html|access-date=May 19, 2016|work=The Plain Dealer|date=May 18, 2016}}</ref> Franchise cinematographer [[Stephen F. Windon]] returned for the eighth instalment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stephenwindon.com/home.html|title=Stephen F. Windon ACS ASC \u2013 CINEMATOGRAPHER|website=StephenWindon.com}}</ref> Filming also took place in [[Atlanta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2017/04/13/how-much-did-fast-furious-8-spend-filming-in.html|title=How much did 'Fast & Furious 8' spend filming in Georgia? (SLIDESHOW)|last=Hensley|first=Ellie|date=April 13, 2017|work=Atlanta Business Chronicle|access-date=March 23, 2018}}</ref> and New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/04/07/fate-furious-exclusive-director-f-gary-gray-new-york-chase/|title='Fate of the Furious' Exclusive: Director F. Gary Gray Previews the Epic New York City Chase|last=Lawrence|first=Derek|date=April 7, 2017|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=October 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\n{{main|The Fate of the Furious (score)|The Fate of the Furious: The Album}}\n[[Brian Tyler]], who scored the third, fourth, fifth, and seventh installments, was tapped to compose the [[film score]] for the eighth picture.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/fast-furious-8-stunts-video-charlize-theron/|title=Fast 8 Stunt Video; Composer Talks Charlize Theron Character|date=June 10, 2016|work=[[Screen Rant]]|accessdate=July 9, 2016}}</ref> A soundtrack album by [[Atlantic Records]] was released on April 14, 2017, coinciding with the film's US theatrical release.<ref>{{cite news|last=Frydenlun|first=Zach|title=Here's ''The Fate of the Furious: The Album'' Soundtrack Tracklist f/ Young Thug, Migos, Travis Scott, and More|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2017/03/fate-of-the-furious-soundtrack-tracklist-exclusive|accessdate=March 10, 2017|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 2, 2017}}</ref> The film's score album was released on April 27, by [[Back Lot Music]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chitwood|first1=Adam|title=Listen to an Exclusive Track from Brian Tyler's ''The Fate of the Furious'' Score|url=http://collider.com/fate-of-the-furious-score-clip-brian-tyler/|accessdate=April 25, 2017|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''The Fate of the Furious'' had its world premiere in [[Berlin]] on April 4, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/hollywood/fate-of-the-furious-to-premiere-at-berlin-on-april-4-fast-and-furious-8-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-4579402/|title=Fate of the Furious to premiere at Berlin on April 4. Vin Diesel shares new poster|work=[[The Indian Express]]|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017}}</ref> The film was theatrically released in the United States on April 14, 2017, playing in [[3D film|3D]], [[IMAX 3D]], and [[4DX]] internationally, and received a day-and-date release across major markets such as Australia, the United Kingdom, China, and [[India]], beginning on April 12, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/universals-fast-8-lands-china-release-date-983382|title=Universal's 'Fast 8' Lands China Release Date (Exclusive)|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 6, 2017|accessdate=March 6, 2017}}</ref> The film was released day-and-date in 1,074 IMAX screens around the world, making it the widest day-and-date opening in IMAX history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4282&p=.htm|title='Boss Baby' Repeats at No. 1 While 'Beauty and the Beast' Closes in on $1 Billion Worldwide|first=Brad |last=Brevet|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' was released on 4K, Blu-ray, DVD, and Digital HD on July 11, 2017, but has yet to be released in 3D Blu-ray.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Fate of the Furious Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/The-Fate-of-the-Furious-Blu-ray/170135/|publisher=[[Blu-ray]]|accessdate=January 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Box office ===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' grossed $226&nbsp;million in the United States and Canada and $1.010&nbsp;billion in other territories for a worldwide total of $1.236&nbsp;billion, against a production budget of $250 million .<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|title=The Fate of the Furious (2017)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=furious8.htm|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=July 14, 2017}}</ref> It is Universal Pictures' most ambitious worldwide distribution release in the studio's history. The film was released day-and-date in 64 territories worldwide, including almost all major markets (minus Japan), starting from April 12, 2017, and was projected to earn anywhere between $375\u2013440&nbsp;million in its five-day opening weekend.<ref name=\"WWW\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-global-opening-box-office-record-furious-7-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202067353/|title='Fate of the Furious' Global Opening Could Leave 'F7's $397M+ Debut in the Dust \u2013 Box Office Preview|first1=Anthony |last1=D'Alessandro |first2=Nancy |last2=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 10, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"V\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-box-office-opening-1202028227/|title='Fate of the Furious' Races Toward Massive $380 Million-Plus Global Box Office Debut|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> By the end of the weekend, it ended up earning $539.9&nbsp;million from nearly 23,000 screens, way above initial projections, to score [[List of highest-grossing openings for films#Biggest worldwide openings since 2002|the biggest global opening in cinematic history]] until it was surpassed by ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' the following year. It also marked the third time that a film earned over $500&nbsp;million in a single weekend, after ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' ($529&nbsp;million) and ''[[Jurassic World]]'' ($525.5&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"F58\"/> In IMAX, the film made $31.1&nbsp;million from 1,079 screens to record the biggest IMAX April debut and the fourth-biggest overall at the time.<ref name=\"F58\"/>\n\nOn April 30, it crossed the $1&nbsp;billion threshold, becoming the second release of 2017 (following ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]''), the fifth film released by [[Universal Pictures]] (after ''[[Jurassic Park (film)|Jurassic Park]]'', ''[[Furious 7]]'', ''[[Jurassic World]]'', and ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'') and the thirtieth film overall in cinematic history to gross over $1&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"1Billion\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/30/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-joins-furious-7-in-the-1-billion-club/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Joins 'Furious 7' In The $1 Billion Club|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-milestone-fate-furious-crosses-1b-globally-998794|title=Box-Office Milestone: 'Fate of the Furious' Crosses $1B Globally|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> It was the third-highest-grossing film of the year, behind ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]'', and ''Beauty and the Beast'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/19/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-zooms-past-logan-to-be-years-second-biggest-hit/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Zooms Past 'Logan' To Be Year's Second Biggest Hit|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 19, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> the second-biggest action film that is not a fantasy or superhero movie, behind ''Furious 7'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/07/box-office-baahubali-2-drops-68-get-out-tops-200m-fate-of-the-furious-passes-skyfall/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Baahubali 2' Drops 68%, 'Get Out' Tops $200M, 'Fate Of The Furious' Passes 'Skyfall'|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 7, 2017|accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref> and was Universal's highest-grossing live-action release since ''Jurassic World'' back in June 2015.<ref name=\"JJ\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/20/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-nears-700-million-worldwide/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Nears $700 Million Worldwide|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''The Fate of the Furious'' concluded 2017 as the third highest-grossing film of the year worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/year/2017/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=Domestic Box Office For 2017|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== North America ====\nLike many of its predecessors, ''The Fate of the Furious'' was released in the United States and Canada in the month of April, and like its immediate predecessor, occupied the lucrative [[Easter week]] holiday period slot, where it was expected to open with $100\u2013125&nbsp;million. It received the widest pre-summer release ever, at an estimated 4,304 venues, besting the 4,242 opening theater count of ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'' the previous March.<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-fate-furious-revs-engines-110m-us-debut-993044|title=Box-Office Preview: 'Fate of the Furious' Revs Engines for $110M-Plus U.S. Debut|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-fate-of-the-furious-20170410-htmlstory.html|title='The Fate of the Furious' could reach $400&nbsp;million in global box office this weekend|first=Ryan |last=Faughnde|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/04/12/fate-furious-box-office-predictions/|title=Box office: Fate of the Furious to speed into top spot|first=Joey |last=Nolfi|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> The film made $10.4&nbsp;million from Thursday night previews from 3,310 theaters, the second-highest of the franchise behind ''[[Furious 7]]''{{'}}s $15.8&nbsp;million.<ref name=DEADopen>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|title='Fate of the Furious' To Clock $100M+ Stateside, As Pic Zooms To All-Time $529M+ Global Debut \u2013 Sunday AM Update|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-opening-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202069983/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> On its opening day it grossed $45.6&nbsp;million, with Thursday previews making up 22.8% of the amount, slightly better than the 23% for ''Furious 7''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/15/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-snags-nos-fueled-45-6m-friday-for-likely-100m-weekend/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Snags Boffo $46M Friday For Likely $100M+ Weekend|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Earning a total of $98.8&nbsp;million on its opening weekend, the film scored the second-biggest opening in the franchise (the third-biggest adjusted for inflation) and the third-biggest April debut, behind ''Furious 7'' and ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]''. It posted an almost identical weekend multiplier like its immediate predecessor (2.166\u00d7 vs 2.18\u00d7).<ref name=\"Mul\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/17/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-steals-record-crushing-532m-worldwide-opening/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Steals Record-Crushing $532M Worldwide Opening|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web|url=https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/04/16/movies/fate-of-the-furious-slows-at-home-but-roars-overseas.html?action=click&contentCollection=movies&region=rank&module=package&version=highlights&contentPlacement=2&pgtype=sectionfront&_r=0&referer=https://www.nytimes.com/section/movies|title='Fate of the Furious' Slows at Home but Roars Overseas|first=Brooks |last=Barnes|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref> However, this is not surprising considering how both films opened over Good Friday/Easter Sunday stretch. Scott Mendelson of ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine compared the opening to how ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]'' (2015) opening fell from ''[[Skyfall]]'' (2012). One notable record the film set was the best opening for a film with an African-American director, with Gray besting his own record set with ''[[Straight Outta Compton (film)|Straight Outta Compton]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/16/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-drifts-to-100m-weekend-spark-bombs/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Drifts To $100M Weekend, 'Spark' Bombs|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nSticking to the franchise's famous and lauded habit of including a multi-ethnic cast of characters, the film played to audiences of all ethnicities. Domestically, [[White people|Caucasians]] made up 41 percent of the audience, followed by [[Hispanics]] (26 percent), African-Americans (21 percent), [[Asians]] (11 percent), and Native American/Other (3 percent), according to comScore's exit polling service PostTrack. The pic skewed male at 58 percent, far more than the last film at 51 percent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-fate-furious-nabs-1002m-us-record-5325m-global-start-994377|title=Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Nabs $100.2M in U.S. for Record $532.5M Global Start|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/fate-of-the-furious-box-office-2-1202031577/|title=Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Debuts to Hefty $100.2 Million|first=Brent |last=Lang|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> 2D ticketbuyers represented 57% of the film's opening compared to its predecessor's 71%. This means more die-hard moviegoers came out to watch the eighth instalment rather than people who do not typically go to the movies.<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nWhile ''The Fate of the Furious''{{'}}s debut is 34% less than its predecessor's opening,<ref name=DEADopen/> critics have noted that the debut is still considered a massive success and not a big letdown given it is the eighth installment in an action franchise. [[Universal Pictures]] was well aware that the robust debut of ''Furious 7'' could not be duplicated<ref name=\"NYTimes\"/> due to the wave of good reviews and publicity over the death of star [[Paul Walker]], as well as the notion that the installment was both a farewell to the actor and a kind of coronation for the franchise as a whole. Nevertheless, the film benefited from Easter holiday business with 74% of all K-12 schools off on [[Good Friday]] as well as a third of the nation's colleges.<ref name=DEADopen/> The film comes out in the wake of its parent franchise celebrating 16 years of availability in cinemas. To wit, few film franchises which are close to 20 years old have demonstrated a box office ability to increase their openings with each installment over time or maintain them in close proximity in terms of debut numbers; [[James Bond in film|''James Bond'' film series]], [[Batman in film|''Batman'' film series]], [[Jurassic Park|''Jurassic Park'' franchise]], and [[List of Star Wars films and television series|''Star Wars'' franchise]].<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nIts hefty opening was followed by the second-biggest April Monday gross ever with $8.5&nbsp;million, behind the seventh installment. Its Sunday to Monday drop was 60% compared to its prequel's 57% drop which is far better than the Monday dropped witnessed by other April releases; ''The Jungle Book'' (\u221276%) and ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' (\u221273%), albeit without the advantage of a school holiday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-april-records-global-box-office-1202071688/|title='Fate of the Furious' Posts Second-Best Monday in April Stateside; Drives Past $600M Worldwide|first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/18/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-racing-past-600-million-worldwide/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Racing Past $600 Million Worldwide|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> Despite the entry of four new [[wide release]]s, critics and box office prognosticators kept a close watch on how much the film would drop in its second weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-promise-unforgettable-no-match-furious-8-995693|title=Box-Office Preview: 'The Promise,' 'Unforgettable' No Match for 'Furious 8'|first=Pamela |last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 20, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> The film fell precipitously on its second Friday earning $11.17&nbsp;million for a 76% drop which is the biggest in the franchise's history, besting the 72% drops for both its two immediate predecessors. The steep decline maybe attributed not because of the onslaught of competitions, but rather due to the polarized reception received by the film and due to just 12% K-12 schools beings off compared to 74% on Good Friday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/22/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-plunges-76-on-friday-still-racing-towards-900m/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Plunges 76% On Friday As It Races Towards $900M|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> It kept its hold at No. 1, albeit dropping about 61% in its sophomore frame for an estimated $38.4&nbsp;million. That domestic drop is right in line with the 59\u201363% drops of the six previous installment in the franchise's on their second weekend out.<ref name=\"SW\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-promise-free-fire-born-in-china-unforgettable-phoenix-forgotten-previews-box-office-1202073216/|title='Fate of the Furious' Drives Five Wide Releases Off The Road With $38.6M Second Weekend \u2013 Sunday AM Update|first1=Anita |last1=Busch |first2=Anthony |last2=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> It topped the box office for three straight weekends, witnessing similar weekend-to-weekend percentage drops like its prequel, albeit earning lesser in terms of numbers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-how-to-be-a-latin-lover-1202079002/|title='Latin Lover' Sets $12M Pantelion Record, 'Baahubali 2' Mighty With $10M+, 'Circle' Is A Square As 'F8' Leads Listless Weekend|first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Outside North America ====\nInternationally, ''The Fate of the Furious'' secured a release in 69 countries.<ref name=\"P1\"/> The film was projected to post an opening between $275\u2013330&nbsp;million from over 20,000 screens, with some analysts believing it could go as high as $350\u2013400&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-international-box-office-first-day-1202030112/|title='Fate of the Furious' Races to $19.7 Million on First Day at International Box Office|first=Dave |last=McNarry|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> It opened Wednesday, April 12, 2017, in 8 countries, earning $17.9&nbsp;million (including previews from 12 countries).<ref name=\"P1\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-international-box-office-opening-1202069413/|title=''Fate of the Furious' Gunning Past $430M Overseas; $534M Worldwide For All-Time Opening Records \u2013 International Box Office|first1=Nancy |last1=Tartaglione |first2=Anita |last2=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 15, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> It opened in 33 more countries on Thursday, April 2, for a total of 41 countries, earning $58.4&nbsp;million, marking Universal Pictures overseas' highest-grossing Thursday ever, and for a two-day total of $82.2&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"P1\"/> It added 22 more countries on Friday, April 3, earning $112.1&nbsp;million to score Universal International's highest-grossing Friday of all time, for a three-day total of $194.8&nbsp;million. The robust Friday take helped Universal push past $1&nbsp;billion internationally in 2017 which is the second-quickest ever and the studio's eleventh consecutive year overall the pass the mark. Moreover, on the same day, the franchise crossed the $4&nbsp;billion milestone.<ref name=\"P1\"/> In total, through Sunday, the film registered an opening of $441.1&nbsp;million from 64 markets, setting new records for the biggest April international debut, Universal's biggest, and the biggest of all time overall (ahead of ''[[Jurassic World]]'')\u2014It is the first such film to open past $400&nbsp;million in a single weekend with a bulk of it coming from China. Around $22.6&nbsp;million came from (681) IMAX screens which is Universal's second-biggest behind only ''Jurassic World''.<ref name=\"F58\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-record-opening-weekend-logan-beauty-and-the-beast-international-box-office-1202070697/|title='Fate of the Furious' Smokes Records With $432.3M Overseas Bow; $532.5M Worldwide \u2013 International Box Office|first1=Nancy |last1=Tartaglione |first2=Anita |last2=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> It topped the international charts for a second consecutive term, adding another $158.1&nbsp;million<ref name=\"F908\"/> after which it was surpassed by ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'', another film starring Diesel and Russell, in its third weekend.<ref name=\"GotG\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-2-china-international-box-office-1202079772/|title='Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2' Zooms With $101.2M Bow \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref> In IMAX, the film has grossed north of $58&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"GotG\"/> On May 28, the film officially passed the $1&nbsp;billion threshold to become the second film in the franchise, following ''Furious 7'', and the sixth film to pass the said mark.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/the-fate-of-the-furious-crossing-1-billion-internationally-1202103559/|title='The Fate of the Furious' Expected To Cross $1B Tomorrow at Int'l Box Office|first=Anita |last=Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 27, 2017|accessdate=May 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/28/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-races-past-1-billion-overseas/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Races Past $1 Billion Overseas|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=May 28, 2017|accessdate=May 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIt set the record for the biggest opening day of 2017 in every territory it has been released at, the biggest opening day of all time in 16 markets, Universal's biggest opening day ever in 22 territories and the biggest opening in the franchise in 38 markets. Moreover, it recorded the biggest paid previews of all time in Malaysia, Singapore, Venezuela, and Vietnam.<ref name=\"P1\"/> In terms of opening weekend, the film debuted at No. 1 in all markets where it set the biggest opening weekend of all time in 20 markets; Universal's biggest opening weekend ever in 28 markets; and the biggest opening in the franchise in 40 markets.<ref name=\"F58\"/><ref name=\"F908\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671/|title='Fate of the Furious' Fires Up $745M Offshore, $908M WW; Tops 'Transformers' In China \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-crosses-1-billion-worldwide-box-office-china-record-biggest-grossing-import-1202079768/|title='Fate of the Furious' Drives Past $1B at Worldwide Box Office; Tops 'Furious 7' For New China Record|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> The top openings were recorded in China ($192&nbsp;million),<ref>{{cite news |title=The Fate of the Furious heading for record global opening |url=https://filmindustry.network/fate-furious-heading-record-global-opening/32264 |publisher=Film Industry Network |date=April 16, 2017}}</ref> Mexico ($17.7&nbsp;million), the UK and Ireland ($17.5&nbsp;million), Russia ($14.2&nbsp;million), Germany ($13.6&nbsp;million), Brazil ($12.8&nbsp;million), India ($10.7&nbsp;million), Korea ($10.6&nbsp;million), Middle East combined ($9.9&nbsp;million), Taiwan ($9.3&nbsp;million), France ($9.2&nbsp;million), Australia ($9.5&nbsp;million), Argentina ($9&nbsp;million), Indonesia ($8.5&nbsp;million), Italy ($6.7&nbsp;million), Malaysia ($6.3&nbsp;million), Spain ($6.1&nbsp;million), Colombia ($4.9&nbsp;million), Thailand ($4.9&nbsp;million), Panama ($4.8&nbsp;million),<ref name=\"F58\"/> Pakistan ($2.5&nbsp;million), and Romania ($1.7&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671|title='Fate of the Furious' Fires Up $745M Offshore, $908M WW; Tops 'Transformers' In China \u2013 International Box Office|first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017}}</ref> Comparing market-to-market performance, ''Furious 7'' had an opening worth $250&nbsp;million without China and Russia while ''The Fate of the Furious'' delivered $228.2&nbsp;million debut, sans the two aforementioned markets.<ref name=\"F58\"/> In Japan, the film debuted with $7.5&nbsp;million. Although that's a new record for the franchise, the film debuted at number three behind Disney's ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' and local film ''[[Detective Conan: Crimson Love Letter]]''\u2014their robust second-weekend earnings blocked the former from taking the top spot, making Japan one of the few markets where the film didn't open at No. 1.<ref name=\"GotG\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/05/03/japan-box-office-blade-of-the-immortal-bombs-detective-conan-keeps-2nd-place|title=Japan Box Office: \"Blade of The Immortal\" Bombs, \"Detective Conan\" Keeps 2nd Place|first=Mikikazu |last=Komatsu|date=May 3, 2017|accessdate=May 4, 2017|work=[[Crunchyroll]]}}</ref>\n\nExpectations were high for the film's performance in China, as its predecessor set notable records and went on to become the biggest film release there (now the biggest Hollywood release). The film was rebranded in Chinese as ''The Fast and the Furious 8'' to make clear its connection to ''Furious 7''. After ticket sales began on April 2, the film pre-sold more than RMB 125 million ($18.1&nbsp;million) worth of tickets before its release, breaking the previous record held by local film ''[[Journey to the West: Conquering the Demons]]'' three months prior. Moreover, it also set a record for the fastest IMAX advance sales, with RMB 16.5&nbsp;million ($2.4&nbsp;million), breaking the previous record held by ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', according to leading local movie site [[Wanda Cinemas|Mtime]].<ref name=\"WWW\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fate-furious-sets-chinese-ticket-presales-record-992694|title='The Fate of the Furious' Sets Chinese Ticket Pre-sales Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/can-fate-furious-beat-furious-7-china-box-office-record/|title=Can 'Fate of the Furious' Beat 'Furious 7' China Box Office Record?|first=Matt |last=Pressberg|work=[[The Wrap]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> In total, it pre-sold around $43.5&nbsp;million tickets two hours before previews began, the biggest ever in the country.<ref name=\"P1\"/> It earned a record-breaking RMB 59.8&nbsp;million ($8.7&nbsp;million) from Thursday paid previews ($8&nbsp;million excluding online ticketing surcharges which now count as grosses), breaking its predecessor's former record of RMB 52.5&nbsp;million ($8.5&nbsp;million in 2015; $7.6&nbsp;million in 2017 exchange rates).<ref name=\"F\">{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/13/box-office-fate-of-the-furious-earns-28m-overseas-revs-engines-for-record-china-debut/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Fate Of The Furious' Earns $28M Overseas, Revs Engines For Record China Debut|first=Scott |last=Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"OPD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fate-furious-smashes-single-day-record-994018|title=China Box Office: 'The Fate of the Furious' Smashes Single-Day Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> On Friday, the film was screened in approximately 158,000 screens, a new record for any film, breaking [[Warcraft (film)|''Warcraft'']]'s former 122,000 screen counts, and almost double the estimated 80,700 screen count of its predecessor.<ref name=\"CFI\">{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/on-screen-china-fate-of-the-furious-peels-out/|title=On Screen China: 'Fate of the Furious' Set To Peel Out|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> By Friday noon, it had already grossed $30&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/furious-8-overtakes-30-million-by-midday-in-china-opening-1202030643/|title='Furious 8' Revs Past $30 Million by Midday in China Opening|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Buoyed by positive word-of-mouth\u20149.4/10 user rating on mobile ticketing platform Maoyan, and 7.4/10 from reviews aggregator [[Douban]]\u2014and effective marketing campaign, it set a new record for the biggest single-day ever at the Chinese box office, including previews. This was achieved at 7 p.m. local time.<ref name=\"OPD\"/> In total, the film grossed an estimated RMB 452.8&nbsp;million ($65.8&nbsp;million) on its opening day, inclusive of previews and online ticketing surcharges, compared to the RMB 398 million ($57.8&nbsp;million) posted by its predecessor. It is the first film in Chinese history to register above RMB 400&nbsp;million ($58&nbsp;million) in a single day.<ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-china-openieg-records-1202030781/|title='Fate of the Furious' Speeds to Record-Breaking $65 Million Opening Day in China|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> Earning a total of RMB 1.323&nbsp;billion ($192.2&nbsp;million), according to Chinese sources and RMB 190 million, according to Universal, in its debut weekend, it set a new milestone for three-day opening weekend and overall the second-best debut ever behind only local pic ''[[The Mermaid (2016 film)|The Mermaid]]'', which had the benefit of four days of previews over the [[Chinese New Year|New Year]] period in February 2016. An estimated $14&nbsp;million came from 395 IMAX screens, the second-biggest-ever in the country, behind ''Warcraft''.<ref name=\"F58\"/> Its three-day debut alone made it the biggest Hollywood release of 2017 and the third-biggest overall. Factoring out online ticketing surcharges, the total comes to a slightly less-hefty RMB 1.245&nbsp;billion ($182.2&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"CFIOP\">{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/china-box-office-furious-8-paves-new-roads/|title=China Box Office: 'Furious 8' Paves New Roads|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> In just nine days, the film passed the historic RMB 2&nbsp;billion ($300&nbsp;million) and thereby became the biggest release of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/fate-of-the-furious-300-million-at-china-box-office-1202392915/|title='Fate of the Furious' Passes $300 Million at China Box Office|first=Patrick |last=Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 22, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> The film fell precipitously by 71.4% in its second weekend (from its $190&nbsp;million debut), earning RMB 374 million ($54.3&nbsp;million) for a massive 10-day total of RMB 2.19&nbsp;billion ($318&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fast-8-races-past-300m-chases-furious-7-all-time-record-996662|title=China Box Office: 'Fast 8' Races Past $300M, Chases 'Furious 7' for All-Time Record|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/china-box-office-smurfs-come-up-short-f8-remains/|title=China Box Office: Smurfs Come Up Short, F8 Remains #1|first=Jonathan |last=Papish|work=China Film Insider|date=April 24, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> On April 30, it became the biggest Hollywood/foreign release of all time with RMB 2.44&nbsp;billion, surpassing its prequels former record of 2.41&nbsp;billion. However, in terms of US currency, ''The Fate of the Furious'' ($381&nbsp;million) is still behind ''Furious 7'' ($391&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"GotG\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-fate-furious-overtakes-furious-7-become-biggest-hollywood-film-ever-998800|title=China Box Office: 'Fate of the Furious' Overtakes 'Furious 7' to Become Biggest Hollywood Film Ever|first=Patrick |last=Brzeski|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017}}</ref> After three consecutive weeks of topping the charts, it slipped to fourth place after being dethroned by ''Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2'' from the top spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/china-box-office-guardians-2-beats-dangal-for-weekend-win-1202411713/|title=China Box Office: 'Guardians 2' Beats India's 'Dangal' For Weekend Win|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=May 7, 2017|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref> It has so far grossed a total of RMB 2.671&nbsp;billion ($392.8&nbsp;million) and is the country's second-biggest grosser ever, behind only ''The Mermaid'' at the time of its release.<ref name=\"JJ\"/>\n\nIn India, the film secured a release across approximately 1,600\u20131,800 screens (1,000\u20131,200 screens fewer than its predecessor). Like other Hollywood releases, it was released in both 2K projections and normal projections, and dubbed in local languages such as Hindi, Tamil and Telugu. It is the first international film to be dubbed into the [[Kannada]] language. Despite clashing with local film ''[[Begum Jaan]]'', analysts believe the two films will not affect each other's performance, as they appeal to distinct moviegoers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/furious-8-might-not-score-100-cr-in-india-begum-jaan-to-remain-unaffected/|title=Furious 8 Might Not Score 100 Cr in India; Begum Jaan To Remain Unaffected|first=Ahana |last=Bhattacharya|work=[[Koimoi]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/vidya-balans-begum-jaan-will-earn-rs-14-crore-over-the-first-weekend-while-dwayne-johnson-vin-diesels-the-fate-of-the-furious-will-rake-in-rs-35-crore/|title=Vidya Balan's Begum Jaan and Dwayne Johnson-Vin Diesel's The Fate of the Furious will rock the box office over the first weekend|author=Karan Shah|work=Hollywood Life|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-furious-8-first-hollywood-film-to-be-dubbed-in-kannada-2398669|title=Fate of the Furious is the first Hollywood film to be dubbed into Kannada|first=Subhash K. |last=Jha|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> Universal had high hopes in the territory, after ''Furious 7'' grossed an unprecedented $24.9&nbsp;million in 2015, and became the biggest foreign release ever in the country at the time of its release (now the second-biggest). The [[Central Board of Film Certification]] gave the film a UA rating (parental guidance suggested for children under 12), rather than an A for adults, after the studio agreed to cut several profanities (CBFC was willing to pass the film with an A certificate with no cuts but Universal wanted a UA certificate leading to the board censoring all profanities with few cuts).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/12/a-fast-and-furious-weekend-ahead-at-indian-cinemas/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=A Fast And Furious Weekend Ahead at Indian Cinemas|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> It earned around {{INRConvert|85.0|m}} net from Wednesday paid previews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/the-fate-of-the-furious-does-good-business-on-paid-previews-at-the-box-office-in-india/|title=The Fate of the Furious Does Good Business On Paid Previews at the Box Office in India|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> The following day it grossed {{INRConvert|225|m}}, including previews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/hollywood/fast-and-furious-8-box-office-collection-diesel-and-dwayne-johnson-film-4613405/|title=Fast and Furious 8 box office collection: Vin Diesel, Dwayne Johnson film earns Rs 22.50 crore in India|first=Samarpita |last=Das|work=[[The Indian Express]]|date=April 14, 2017|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref> On its official opening day, it grossed {{INRConvert|161|m}} for a three-day total of {{INRConvert|386|m}}.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|number=853222969748869120|title=#Furious8 Wed previews 8.50 cr, Thu 14 cr, Fri 16.10 cr. Total: \u20b9 38.60 cr [note: Gross BO]. India biz. AWESOME! #TheFateOfTheFurious|authorlink=Taran Adarsh|last=Adarsh|first=Taran|date=April 15, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2018}}</ref> Earning a total of $10.7&nbsp;million, it set a new record for the biggest-ever foreign opening in the country, toppling its prequel's former record. As such, it is the first foreign film to open north of $10&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"P1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/16/gippy-grewal-and-tamil-stars-raghava-arya-and-rajkiran-battle-for-audiences-in-india/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Gippy Grewal And Tamil Stars Raghava, Arya And Rajkiran Battle For Audiences in India|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 17, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> Following its record breaking opening, it fell about 58% on its second weekend excluding previews, earning another $4&nbsp;million for a two-weekend total of over $17.4&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/04/23/raveena-tandon-rape-drama-maatr-sets-out-to-shock-and-succeeds/?c=0&s=BoxOffice|title=Raveena Tandon Rape Drama 'Maatr' Sets Out To Shock \u2013 And Succeeds|first=Don |last=Groves|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 24, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> With over $19.2&nbsp;million it is currently the biggest foreign release of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-fast-furious-8-becomes-highest-hollywood-grosser-2017-india-box-office-2/|title=Box Office: Fast and Furious 8 becomes the highest Hollywood grosser of 2017 at the India box office|author=Bollywood Hungama News Network|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=April 25, 2017}}</ref> However, in terms of net earnings\u2014which is the base for box office calculations in India\u2014the film was unable to break past the {{INRConvert|1|b}} mark, stalling at around {{INRConvert|856|m}}. Despite a record breaking opening, it lost significant amount of screen counts and audiences thereafter, partly due to the release of ''[[Baahubali 2: The Conclusion|Baahubali: The Conclusion]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-baahubali-2-conclusion-mania-engulfs-fast-furious-8-prevents-entering-100-cr-club-india-box-office/|title=Box Office: Baahubali 2 \u2013 The Conclusion mania engulfs Fast and Furious 8; prevents it from entering 100 cr. club at the India box office|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=May 6, 2017|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe biggest-earning markets are China ($392.8&nbsp;million), followed by Brazil ($41.8&nbsp;million), the UK and Ireland ($37.5&nbsp;million), Mexico ($36.8&nbsp;million) and Germany ($32.4&nbsp;million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=furious8.htm|title=The Fate of the Furious (2017) \u2013 International Box Office Results \u2013 Box Office Mojo|website=boxofficemojo.com|access-date=13 May 2018}}</ref> In Peru, it has become Universal's highest-grossing film ever.<ref name=\"Jap60\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-marvel-11-billion-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-international-china-box-office-weekend-1202086302/|title='Guardians 2' Notches $428M Global, Lifts MCU Past $11B; 'Furious 8' Tops $950M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|date=May 7, 2017|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref> With over $1&nbsp;billion in international receipts and representing a boffo 82% of the film's total worldwide gross, it is currently the seventh-biggest overseas earner behind ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', ''[[Titanic (1997 film)|Titanic]]'', ''Furious 7'', ''Star Wars: The Force Awakens'', and ''Jurassic World''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/?pagenum=1&sort=osgross&order=DESC&p=.htm|title=WORLDWIDE GROSSES|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\n''The Fate of the Furious'' received mixed reviews.<ref name=\"reviews1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/love-sex/critics-give-mixed-reviews-to-the-fate-of-the-furious/vp-BBzQxFI |title=Critics Give Mixed Reviews To 'The Fate of the Furious'|work=MSN News|publisher=[[MSN]]|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"reviews2\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/fate-of-the-furious-reviews-round-up-1202027165/ |title=Fate of the Furious' Reviews: What the Critics Are Saying|work=Variety|accessdate=April 16, 2017|date=April 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Dickey|first1=Josh|title=Critics can't agree if 'Fate of the Furious' is fantastic or a pile of garbage|url=http://mashable.com/2017/04/09/fate-furious-8-reviews-movies-roundup/|accessdate=January 14, 2018|work=[[Mashable]]|date=April 10, 2017}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 67% based on 301 reviews, and an [[average rating]] of 6.13/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''The Fate of the Furious'' opens a new chapter in the franchise, fueled by the same infectious cast chemistry and over-the-top action fans have come to expect.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_fate_of_the_furious |title=The Fate of the Furious (2017) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score 56 out of 100, based on 45 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-fate-of-the-furious |title=The Fate of the Furious Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=April 20, 2017}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale,<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite tweet|user=CinemaScore |number=853100097802055680 |title=Congratulations on your A #cinemascore grade! @KristoferHivju @Kurtrussell @Nealmoritz #FateandtheFurious |author=[[CinemaScore]] |date=April 14, 2017 |accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it an 88% overall positive score and a 71% \"definite recommend.\"<ref name=DEADopen/>\n\nMike Ryan of ''[[Uproxx]]'' gave the film a positive review, writing: \"This isn't my favorite of the series\u2014that's still ''[[Furious 7]]'' (it's hard to top those jumps from skyscraper to skyscraper, but this is a worthy entry). These movies know what they are. These movies know they are fun. These are fun movies!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/movies/the-fate-of-the-furious-review/ |title='The Fate of the Furious': This Time They Fight A Submarine |website=[[Uproxx]] |date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref> [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', in his positive review of the film, wrote: \"Most franchises, after eight films, are feeling a twinge of exhaustion, but this one has achieved a level of success\u2014and perpetual kinetic creative energy\u2014that's a testament to its commercial/cultural/demographic resonance.\" He also wrote, \"If this series, over the last 16 years, has taught us anything, it's that just when you think it's about to run out of gas, it gets outfitted with an even more elaborate fuel-injection system.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-vin-diesel-dwayne-johnson-1202026947/|title=Film Review: 'The Fate of the Furious' |date=April 9, 2017|last=Gleiberman |first=Owen|authorlink=Owen Gleiberman|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\nDavid Ehrlich of [[IndieWire]] gave the film a C\u2212 and called it the worst entry of the franchise, saying: \"As much a mess of conflicting tones and styles as it is of locations, this setpiece\u2014like the rest of Gray's movie\u2014feels like a heap of random parts that were thrown together in the hopes that fate might somehow weld them into a roadworthy vehicle. But it's not all groundbreaking.\"<ref>{{cite web|first=David |last=Ehrlich |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/04/the-fate-of-the-furious-review-vin-diesel-the-rock-charlize-theron-worst-fast-and-furious-movie-1201803492/ |title='The Fate of the Furious' Review: Vin Diesel's Family Becomes Dysfunctional in Worst 'Fast and Furious' Ever |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=April 9, 2017 |accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref> J. R. Kinnard of ''[[PopMatters]]'' magazine gave a lukewarm review, writing: \"It's unlikely that devotees will consider ''The Fate of the Furious'' one of the stronger entries in the series. Still, the filmmakers and actors are clearly dedicated to making a quality product, avoiding the complacency that often plagues action sequels.\"<ref name=PM>{{cite web|work=[[PopMatters]]|last=Kinnard |first=J.R.|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/the-fate-of-the-furious-f-gary-gray-van-disel-meets-crocodile/|title='The Fate of the Furious' Dom (Vin Diesel) Meets the Crocodile|date=April 13, 2017}}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film 2 out of 4 stars, saying: \"Moments after Dom has gone rogue and apparently wants to kill them, they're making jokes. As they're racing through the streets of New York City or skidding along the ice in Russia, killing bad guys and narrowly avoiding getting killed themselves, they're crackin' wise. Even within this ludicrous universe, it's jarring to hear these supposedly smart folks, who refer to themselves as 'family,' acting like idiots who don't seem to care if they live or die, or if their friends survive.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/overlong-idiotic-fate-of-the-furious-drags-down-the-franchise/ |title=Overlong, idiotic 'Fate of the Furious' drags down the franchise |newspaper=[[Chicago Sun-Times]] | authorlink=Richard Roeper| author=Roeper, Richard| date=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nProfessor of international [[political economy]] Richard E. Feinberg has commented on the political significance of the film's opening setting of [[Havana]] in the context of shifting [[Cuba\u2013United States relations|U.S.\u2013Cuban relations]], calling the eighth instalment, \"Hollywood's love letter to Havana\".<ref name=\"Feinberg\">{{cite web|url=https://cubacounterpoints.com/archives/5368|title=Fast and Furious 8: Hollywood's Love Letter to Havana|last=Feinberg|first=Richard E.|date=May 4, 2017|website=cubacounterpoints.com|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref> He writes, \"In the Cuban sequence's dramatic climax, Dom wins his hard-fought one-mile race (\"a Cuban mile\") against a tough local competitor, by a nose. The loser is gracious: 'You won my car and you earned my respect,' he admits to the FF hero. Dom's response is equally magnanimous: 'Keep your car, your respect is good enough for me.' In this instance, FF8 captures the essence of the relations between the United States and Cuba: it's all about mutual respect.\"<ref name=\"Feinberg\" />\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"6\"| [[2017 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie - Action|Choice Movie: Action]]\n!\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Choice Movie Actor: Action\n| [[Vin Diesel]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Actress: Action\n| [[Michelle Rodriguez]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain|Choice Movie: Villain]]\n| [[Charlize Theron]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie: Ship\n| Michelle Rodriguez and Vin Diesel\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[44th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Action or Adventure Film|Best Action or Adventure Film]]\n| ''The Fate of the Furious''\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|title='Black Panther,' 'Walking Dead' Rule Saturn Awards Nominations|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 15, 2018|accessdate=March 15, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6xwc1azco?url=http://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|archivedate=March 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]\n| [[Christian Wagner]] and [[Paul Rubell]]\n|}\n\n== Sequel ==\n{{Main|F9 (film)}}\nOn February 3, 2016, Universal Pictures set initial release dates for the two remaining films in the franchise, with the first, ''[[F9 (film)|F9]]'', given an initial release date of April 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rahman|first=Abid|title=Universal Sets Dates for 'Fast & Furious' Parts 9 and 10|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/fast-furious-8-9-10-861585|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=February 3, 2016 |accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref> However, on October 4, 2017, the release date was pushed back to April 10, 2020, to accommodate for the spin-off film ''[[Hobbs & Shaw]]'',<ref name=\"Sequels\">{{cite web|last=Dornbush|first=Jonathon|title=FAST AND FURIOUS 9 RELEASE DATE DELAYED|url=http://m.ign.com/articles/2017/10/04/fast-and-furious-9-release-date-delayed|work=[[IGN]]|date=October 4, 2017 |accessdate=October 5, 2017}}</ref> which was released on August 2, 2019.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|title='Fast & Furious' Spinoff With Dwayne Johnson & Jason Statham Shifts to August 2019|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/dwayne-johnson-jason-statham-fast-furious-spin-off-summer-2019-release-1202182987/|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 9, 2018|accessdate=May 15, 2018}}</ref> The announcement of the spin-off provoked a response on [[Instagram]] by [[Tyrese Gibson]], criticizing [[Dwayne Johnson]] and [[Seven Bucks Productions]] co-creator Hiram Garcia (who served as producers for the spin-off) for causing the ninth film to be delayed for another year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fast & Furious: The Rock And Jason Statham Spin-Off Coming In 2019|url=https://whatculture.com/film/fast-furious-the-rock-and-jason-statham-spin-off-coming-in-2019|work=WhatCulture.com|date=October 6, 2017|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref> ''F9'' was then pushed back to April 2, 2021 as a result of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=N}}\n \n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{official website|http://www.fastandfurious.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|4630562}}\n* {{AllMovie title|643403}}\n\n{{The Fast and the Furious}}\n{{F. Gary Gray}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fate of the Furious, The}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s chase films]]\n[[Category:2010s heist films]]\n[[Category:2010s road movies]]\n[[Category:2010s sequel films]]\n[[Category:Action films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American action thriller films]]\n[[Category:American chase films]]\n[[Category:Original Film films]]\n[[Category:American heist films]]\n[[Category:American road movies]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:China Film Group Corporation films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Fast & Furious]]\n[[Category:Films about automobiles]]\n[[Category:Films about nuclear war and weapons]]\n[[Category:Films about terrorism]]\n[[Category:Films directed by F. Gary Gray]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Neal H. Moritz]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Brian Tyler]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Films set in Havana]]\n[[Category:Films set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Films set on airplanes]]\n[[Category:Films set in prison]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Arctic]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Havana]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Iceland]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Cleveland]]\n[[Category:Films