lbert is the son of former NFL quarterback [[Gale Gilbert]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.statesman.com/sports/content/sports/stories/highschool/12/07/1207bohls.html |title=Lake Travis' Gilbert is a grounded but premier passer |last=Bohls |first=Kirk |date=December 7, 2007 |work=[[Austin American-Statesman]] |access-date=February 23, 2008 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120912211033/http://www.statesman.com/sports/content/sports/stories/highschool/12/07/1207bohls.html |archive-date=September 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe was born in [[Buffalo, New York]], where his father played for the [[Buffalo Bills|Bills]] in the early 1990s as part of the infamous squad that [[Four Falls of Buffalo|lost four straight Super Bowls]]. He moved to [[San Diego, California]], at age three, when Gale signed with the [[San Diego Chargers|Chargers]] (who coincidentally played in the Super Bowl that same year, resulting in a record fifth consecutive championship loss for a player). The family later moved to Austin, Texas, in 1996. Garrett has one brother, Griffin, who played football at [[Texas Christian University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://gofrogs.com/sports/football/roster/griffin-gilbert/1397 |title=Griffin Gilbert - Football |website=TCU Athletics |language=en |access-date=December 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121211074455/http://www.smumustangs.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gilbert_garrett00.html SMU Mustangs bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090802004544/http://www.mackbrown-texasfootball.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/gilbert_garrett00.html Texas Longhorns bio]\n* {{youtube|EHwBirQRVBc|Highlights from Gilbert's high school sophomore season}}\n\n{{Cleveland Browns roster navbox}}\n{{Navboxes| title = Garrett Gibert\u2014awards, championships, and honors\n|list1 = \n{{Mr. Football USA}}\n{{USA Today OPOY}}\n{{Gatorade Football Player of the Year}}\n{{Gatorade National Athlete of the Year}}\n{{Texa