" | 48\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 98\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 49.0\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 481\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 65.9\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | -1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | NFL totals\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 198\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 3,487\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 6,261\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 55.7\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 40,922\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 208\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 196\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | '''73.8'''\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 374\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 686\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 10\n|}\n\n===Playoffs===\n{| BORDER=\"0\" CELLPADDING=\"3\" CELLSPACING=\"0\" ID=\"Table3\"\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"7\" | Passing\n! ALIGN=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | &nbsp;\n! ALIGN=\"center\" colspan=\"3\" | Rushing\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Season\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Team\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | League\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | GP\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Comp\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Att\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Pct\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Yds\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | TD\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | INT\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Att\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | Yds\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | TD\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[NFL playoffs, 1996-97|1996]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | CAR\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NFL\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 2\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 31\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 59\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 52.5\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 315\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 3\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 3\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 7\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 4\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[NFL playoffs, 2000-01|2000]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NYG\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NFL\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 3\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 56\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 98\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 57.1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 622\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 6\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 14\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 26\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[NFL playoffs, 2002-03|2002]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NYG\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NFL\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 29\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 43\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 67.4\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 342\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 4\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | [[NFL playoffs, 2008-09|2008]]\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | TEN\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | NFL\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 29\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 42\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 61.9\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 281\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 1\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n| ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | Playoff totals\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 7\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 145\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 242\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 59.7\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 1,560\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 12\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 11\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 22\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 30\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 0\n|}\n\n==Major League Baseball Draft==\n\nCollins was drafted by the [[Detroit Tigers]] in the 26th round of the 1990 MLB draft, but opted to attend Penn State. Detroit selected him in the 60th round of the 1991 amateur draft, but he did not sign with the club. He was again selected in the 48th round of the 1994 amateur draft by the Toronto Blue Jays but again did not sign.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kerry Collins \u2013 BR Bullpen|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Kerry_Collins|website=baseball-reference.com|accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n===Battles with alcoholism===\nBefore the 1997 season got underway, Collins's private battle with [[alcoholism]] started to make public headlines.  In a highly publicized incident, on the last night of [[Carolina Panthers]] training camp in 1997, Collins used the racial slur \"[[nigger]]\" in reference to [[African-American|black]] teammate [[Muhsin Muhammad]] while in a drunken state at a bar in [[Spartanburg, South Carolina]]. Supposedly, Collins also inadvertently slurred offensive lineman [[Norberto Garrido]], who is of [[Hispanic]] descent. It was widely rumored that Garrido punched Collins in the eye as a result, although this was later proven false.<ref name=\"Panthers' Collins Finds Himself Tangled Up in Racial Barbs\">{{cite news | title = Panthers' Collins Finds Himself Tangled Up in Racial Barbs | first = Mike | last = Freeman | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/24/sports/panthers-collins-finds-himself-tangled-up-in-racial-barbs.html | newspaper = New York Times | date = August 24, 1997 | accessdate = October 3, 2009}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2, 1998, Collins was arrested for drunk driving in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Collins' DWI Case On Hold | url = https://www.cbsnews.com/news/collins-dwi-case-on-hold/ | website = CBS News | date = February 15, 1999 | accessdate = December 20, 2019}}</ref> He finished the 1998 season in New Orleans and signed with the [[New York Giants]] as a free agent on February 19, 1999.<ref>{{cite news | title = Giants Sign QB Kerry Collins | url = https://www.cbsnews.com/news/giants-sign-qb-kerry-collins/ | website = CBS News | date = February 19, 1999 | accessdate = December 20, 2019}}</ref>  Not long before signing with New York, Collins decided to seek treatment for his alcoholism. He entered a rehabilitation clinic in [[Topeka, Kansas]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Uncorked: Kerry Collins Couldn't Release His Bottled Up Talent Until He Let Go of Alcohol | first = Mark | last = Gaughan | url = https://buffalonews.com/2001/01/26/uncorked-kerry-collins-couldnt-release-his-bottled-up-talent-until-he-let-go-of-alcohol/ | newspaper = The Buffalo News | date = January 26, 2001 | accessdate = December 20, 2019}}</ref>\n[[File:FEMA - 44079 - Tennessee Titans helping residents in Tennessee.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Collins in [[Nashville]] helping clean out homes after floods damaged the city]]\nWhile a member of the New York Giants, Collins remained in therapy for four years. As a member of the [[Tennessee Titans]], he readdressed the 1997 racial slur incident, explaining that \"The guys were talking to each other that way, and I was trying to be funny and thought I could do it, too. I was so upset by it. It was bad judgment. I could have been labeled a racist for the rest of my career. I had to live with the way I used that word with a teammate. Extremely poor judgment. I was na\u00efve to think I could use that word in any context.\"<ref name=\"Young's mentor is right next to him, if only he'd reach out\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story?id=09000d5d80b1c033&template=with-video&confirm=true |title=Young's mentor is right next to him, if only he'd reach out |last=George |first=Thomas |date=September 25, 2008 |access-date=September 25, 2008 |publisher=NFL.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of NCAA major college football yearly passing leaders]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n*Reed, Steve (January 27, 2001). [http://www.gazettearchives.com/panthers2001/_article/00000335.htm Once a lost soul, Collins turns career, life around] ''The Gaston Gazette''\n*Gay, Nancy (October 3, 2004). [http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2004/10/03/RAIDERS.TMP Collins appreciates second chances] ''San Francisco Chronicle''\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [http://www.titansonline.com/team/roster/Kerry-Collins/5aab2a78-008b-4d1c-bfc1-7831afc1a00d Tennessee Titans bio]\n* {{espn nfl|id=734|name=Kerry Collins}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Kerry Collins|list1=\n{{Penn State Nittany Lions quarterback navbox}}\n{{1994 NCAA Division I-A College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{Davey O'Brien Award}}\n{{Maxwell Award Winners}}\n{{Chicago Tribune Silver Football navbox}}\n{{NFL Quarterbacks with a Perfect Passer Rating}}\n{{1995 NFL Draft}}\n{{Panthers1995DraftPicks}}\n{{PanthersFirstPick}}\n{{1995 Carolina Panthers}}\n{{Carolina Panthers starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{New Orleans Saints starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{New York Giants starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{Oakland Raiders starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{Tennessee Titans starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{Indianapolis Colts starting quarterback navbox}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Collins, Kerry}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football quarterbacks]]\n[[Category:Carolina Panthers players]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Colts players]]\n[[Category:New Orleans Saints players]]\n[[Category:New York Giants players]]\n[[Category:Oakland Raiders players]]\n[[Category:Penn State Nittany Lions football players]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Titans players]]\n[[Category:All-American college football players]]\n[[Category:Maxwell Award winners]]\n[[Category:People from Berks County, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:People from Lebanon, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Pennsylvania]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1006:b12b:3773:3858:6c02:8a78:da39", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kerry_Collins"}
{"title_page": "Andy Ellison", "text_new": "{{short description|British musician and vocalist|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=December 2010}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                =Andy Ellison\n| image              = Andy Ellison.jpg\n| caption            = Andy Ellison (front) at the Marc Bolan celebration concert\n| image_size         = 250px\n| background          =solo_singer\n| birth_name          =\n| alias               =\n| birth_date                = {{Birth date and age|1945|7|5|df=yes}}\n|birth_place = [[Finchley]], [[London]], [[England]]\n| death_date                =\n| death_place         =\n| origin              =\n| instrument          =\n| genre               =\n| occupation          =\n| years_active        = 1965\u2013present\n| label               =[[Track Records]] etc.\n| associated_acts     =[[John's Children]], [[Jet (UK band)|Jet]], [[Radio Stars]]\n| website                 =[http://www.johnschildren.co.uk johnschildren.co.uk]\n}}\n'''Andrew \"Andy\" Ellison''' (born 5 July 1945 from [[Finchley]]) is a British [[musician]] and [[singing|vocalist]] best known as the [[frontman]] in [[John's Children]], [[Jet (UK band)|Jet]] and [[Radio Stars]].\n\nJohn's Children also featured [[Marc Bolan]] and [[Chris Townson]].\nA [[song]] sung by Ellison, \"It's Been A Long Time,\" appears on the [[soundtrack]] - better known for its contributions from [[The Spencer Davis Group]] and [[Traffic (band)|Traffic]] - to the [[film]], ''[[Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush (film)|Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush]]''. \"It's Been A Long Time\" also featured on the [[compilation album]], ''Backtrack 1'', a [[Track Records]] release featuring The Who and [[Jimi Hendrix]] amongst others.\n\nJet released a single album on CBS Records in 1975, toured as support to Hunter-Ronson and then became [[Radio Stars]],<ref>[http://www.radio-stars.com/ Radio-stars.com]</ref> who had one [[United Kingdom|UK]] [[Top 40]] [[hit record|hit]], \"Nervous Wreck\" in early 1978. It peaked at #39.{{cn|date=December 2019}} The [[A-side and B-side|b-side]] to the [[single (music)|single]] was a cover of [[Marc Bolan]]'s \"Horrible Breath\", a John's Children staple.\n\n\n==Discography==\n*''Cornflake Zoo - solo singles, demos, and rarities'' - [[Compact disc|CD]] - [[Voiceprint Records|Voiceprint]] VP364CD Release date: 11 September 2006 <ref>[http://www.voiceprint.co.uk/web/Release/VP364CD/  Voiceprint CD] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070807021513/http://www.voiceprint.co.uk/web/Release/VP364CD/ |date=August 7, 2007 }}</ref>\n#\"[[You Can't Do That]]\" ([[Lennon\u2013McCartney]])\n#\"Cornflake Zoo\"\n#\"Hippy Gumbo\" ([[Marc Bolan]])\n#\"It's Been A Long Time\"\n#\"Casbah Candy\"\n#\"[[Help! (song)|Help!]]\" (Lennon\u2013McCartney)\n#\"Fool From Upper Eden\"\n#\"Lucky Lie\"\n#\"Train In My Head\"\n#\"To The Beat of A Different Drummer\"\n#\"Life's Too Short\"\n#\"Hurt Myself\"\n#\"She's So Dissatisfied\"\n#\"Something She Said\"\n#\"Heather Lane\"\n#\"Anyway Goodbye\"\n\n*''Fourplay'' - self-published, 2008. [[CD-R]] [[Gramophone record|EP]] featuring four new [[solo (music)|solo]] [[sound recording and reproduction|recordings]] [[songwriter|written]], recorded and [[record producer|produced]] by Ellison in 2007.\n#\"Anyway Goodbye\"\n#\"She's Trying To Kill Me\"\n#\"Cold Light\"\n#\"Cluster Bombs\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.johnschildren.co.uk Official site]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ellison, Andy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:People from Finchley]]\n[[Category:People from Leatherhead]]\n[[Category:English pop singers]]\n[[Category:English male singers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British musician and vocalist|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=December 2010}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:Wiki